title: canned beans
directions: Let the solution strike to boil, then put in beans; boil for 30 minutes.
Put beans in can (jar) seal.
When ready to eat, wash beans about three times in cold water before cooking.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix well before pouring over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine and put in casserole, covered.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Set oven at 350°.
Place casserole in cold oven and bake 1 hour.
Don't brown sausage.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a gallon jar after first mixing the vinegar and sugar together to dissolve sugar.
Cover for 24 hours before using.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well until a soft dough.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut out.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Yields about 100 cookies.

title: pizza style mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems; chop finely.
Saute onion, garlic, green pepper, pepperoni and mushroom stems in olive oil. Cook until soft.
Add chicken broth, bread crumbs (made in blender) with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook until liquid is absorbed. Stuff mixture into mushroom caps.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Add salt.
Chill until partially set.
Add other ingredients. Chill until firm.
Use 1 1/2-quart mold.

title: mountain pudding
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour batter into butter (do not stir). Add can of fruit.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix thawed lemonade and Eagle Brand milk; add Cool Whip.
Use a few drops of green food coloring.
Pour into crust and freeze.

title: swedish hash casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion (drain).
Add other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until rice and vegetables are done at 350°.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish (8-inches square) and set aside.
Separate biscuits and place on top of chicken mixture.
Bake in a 450° oven for 20 minutes, covered loosely with foil about halfway through.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt mayo and cheese in double boiler.
Add crab meat.
Stir. Keep warm in a chafing dish.
Good with Triscuits crackers.

title: hot mushroom dip
directions: The food processor is a must for speed.
Leave onions chunky and peppers very minced, etc.

title: hot nacho cheese dip
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, layer the ingredients in order listed. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, until all the cheeses have melted and the mixture is heated through.
Serve with lots of nachos.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all together in a long pan. Cover top with cornflakes or potato chips (crumbled). Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: glazed ham
directions: Bake ham in usual way.
Thirty minutes before it's done, remove from oven.
Score ham and cover with mixture of mustard, brown sugar and pineapple juice.
Decorate with pineapple slices. Continue to bake for 30 minutes longer to brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Salt and pepper meat; roll in flour.
Cook meat until brown (lots of flour makes gravy).
Put all together the onion, celery and consomme.
Cook for 5 hours or so, slowly.
Watch and stir. Cook rice as directed; put the steak on top to serve.

title: award winning chili (beans)
directions: Soak beans with 1 tablespoon baking soda and clean as usual. Cook until beans are firm, not soft.
Add other ingredients, except the salsa, early in the process of cooking.
Near the end of the cooking time, you judge, add the entire contents of the salsa. The beans are best if not mushy. Stir often while cooking.

title: holland rusk torte
directions: Roll rusk.
Add sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Reserve 1/2 cup of this.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with remainder.
Cook egg yolks, salt, cornstarch, sugar and milk in double boiler.
Cool custard in bain-marie before lining crust.
Put custard in crust.
Beat egg whites and 3 tablespoons sugar, adding one tablespoon at a time.
Cover custard.
Make sure to seal egg whites properly around custard.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Baking in a smaller pan makes the torte deeper.
A 9 x 13-inch pan is very shallow.

title: cranberry jewel salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and
stir in applesauce.
Gradually add cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Cool until partially set. Stir in chopped celery.
Gently fold in cranberry sauce cubes. Pour in mold.
Chill until firm.

title: german scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Cook onion in dripping until tender.
Add spinach; heat through.
In 2-quart or 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, mix potatoes and dry sauce mix from package. Stir in boiling water and milk, omitting margarine from directions.
Stir in bacon, spinach mixture and caraway seed. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese for 2 to 3 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Slice meat 1/4-inch to 3/8-inch thick.
Mix together all remaining ingredients.
Add meat and let marinate for 1 to 2 hours.
Drain meat and place in oven on rack for 8 to 10 hours at 150°.
Check periodically after 7 hours to suit texture desired. This process can also be done in a dehydrator at the same temperature and time.

title: quick garlic sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease a large cookie sheet.
In small saucepan over medium heat, heat butter, parsley and garlic salt just until butter is melted.
Cut each biscuit in half.
With hands roll each half into a stick with butter mixture.
Place on cookie sheet about 1 -inch apart.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes until golden. Makes 20 bread sticks.

title: chicken pepper pasta
directions: In 12-inch skillet, melt butter.
Stir in onion, peppers and garlic.
Cook over medium high heat until peppers are crisply tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from skillet with slotted spoon; set aside, reserving juices in pan.
Add chicken, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until chicken is lightly browned, 7 to 9 minutes.
Prepare vermicelli per package instructions; drain.
Add vegetables, half and half and cheeses to chicken mixture; reduce heat to medium and cook until cheese has melted, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add vermicelli; toss gently to coat.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage apple stuffing
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan over medium heat, brown 1 pound sausage, breaking apart with a fork.
Remove from heat and drain off fat, all but 1/4 cup.
Set aside.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix sugar and pineapple together.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O and water.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Add Cool Whip, cheese and pecans.
Let refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: shabu shabu
directions: In a small bowl, you should have soy sauce and lemon juice 2 to 1, as a dipping sauce.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Cut cabbage in thin slices and crisscross.
Cut up green onions.
Toast nuts and sesame seed lightly.
Prepare dressing.

title: the hawaiian christmas pie
directions: Melt margarine and sugar; add graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well and spread in oblong dish.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix grated cheese with bread crumbs. Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Moisten with water. Can add stems.
Fill crowns and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in mushroom soup.

title: sauce for strawberries
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute. Cool.
Pour sliced strawberries over pound cake, sprinkle with Heath pieces and drizzle with sauce.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, salt and milk.
Cool to lukewarm by adding the cold water.
Dissolve yeast in mixture.
Blend in egg. Add flour and mix well.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add green pepper, onion and cheese. Mix together.
Pour into pie shell.
Whip eggs and half and half; pour over sausage.
Bake in a 375° preheated oven for 40 minutes.

title: southwestern pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Use premade crust or homemade.
Mix chicken and salsa.
Sprinkle crust with 3/4 cup of the cheese.
Top with onion, chicken mixture and pepper.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until crust is brown and cheese is bubbly.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and line with whole graham crackers, set aside.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add all of the beans (don't drain them).
Add brown and white sugar and ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: minute muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; blend until smooth.
Fill greased muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: italian style baked beans
directions: Wash Great Northern beans and cover with cold water.
Allow to stand overnight.
Add dry mustard to remove snappers.
Place over high heat, adding butter to keep down foaming.
Bring to boiling point.
Cover and reduce heat, so water will simmer.
Stir carefully a time or two.
After 1 hour, add salt.
Continue cooking another 1/2 to 1 hour until beans are tender, but not mushy.
Drain cooked beans, saving liquid.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese, pimento cheese and Cheddar cheese soften. Mix all ingredients together and roll into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped pecans.

title: sweet potato compote
directions: Put potatoes in blender or mixer.
Add rest of ingredients and combine until creamy.
(You may need to clean beaters of strings.) You may add sugar to taste or 1/2 cup raisins.
Pour into buttered casserole and top with topping if desired.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: crepes
directions: Sift 1 1/3 cups flour into a deep bowl.
Add milk, a little bit at a time until well blended.
Add eggs, salt and melted butter.
Cover with foil and keep refrigerated for at least 12 hours.
Let oil or butter run evenly into ridges of omelet pan. Oil has reached the desired temperature if a drop of water splashes up.
Pour about 1/4 cup of batter into the lower part of tilted pan, then tilt back in opposite direction.
When bottom of crepe is brown, shake pan to loosen the crepe and turn.
Cook very briefly on the other side.

title: chicken picatta
directions: Dissolve chicken soup supplement in water; pour into frying pan.
Add lemon juice, garlic powder and chicken.
Saute each side for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove chicken to warm plate and cover.
Place mushrooms in frying pan, adding more water and garlic powder if necessary.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken and serve.

title: hot cider
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cider.
Tie spices in small piece of cheesecloth, add to cider.
Slowly bring to boil; cover and simmer.
(May be simmered and served from Crock Pot.)

title: cheesy beef and pasta
directions: Cook pasta per package directions; drain.
In skillet, brown meat, salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Add tomatoes; cook uncovered until slightly thickened.
Stir in onions, green pepper and cream cheese.
Cook until cream cheese melts; add mushrooms. Toss with remaining ingredients.
Cover 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Drain peaches and pineapple.
Heat juice in a saucepan.
Add Jell-O and stir to dissolve.
Add and dissolve softened gelatin. Add baby peaches, peach slices and pineapple.
Place half this mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Spread over the sour cream.
Carefully pour over this the other half of the Jell-O mixture.
Chill until set.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar with mixer. Mix the hot water, jello and Carnation milk. Crumble the graham crackers with the soft butter. Line bottom of oblong cake pan. Add jello mixture to cream cheese mixture. Add whipped cream and pour into lined pan. Add remaining crumbs on top. Place in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Heat beans and drain.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole and add a dab of butter.
Mix the brown sugar and mustard; sprinkle over beans.
Stir in molasses.
Finally, pour sour cream over all and mix gently.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: hello dolly
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan in oven.
Spread 1 cup graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Put 1 cup coconut, 1 cup chocolate chips, 1 cup chopped pecans and 1 can Eagle Brand and drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, mustard, celery seed and salt and pepper; mix well.
Add potatoes, eggs, onion and pickles.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix lemon jello, cherry jello, sugar and boiling water; cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan; refrigerate for several hours, then cut into squares.

title: peanut buster parfait dessert
directions: Mix together Oreo cookie crumbs and melted oleo well; press in 9 x 13-inch pan, then freeze. Soften ice cream.

Put over Oreo mixture, then freeze. Top with a jar of Kraft hot fudge. Sprinkle with chopped peanuts, then freeze. Just before serving, top with Cool Whip, drizzle chocolate syrup on top and sprinkle with crushed pecans or peanuts on top.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger; add onions and celery, cook until tender. Add tomato soup and catsup.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper, if wanted.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, except brown sugar and nuts, in large bowl. Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back or pulls away from pan.
Spoon hot glaze over warm cake.
Serve warm or cool with Cool Whip.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into first mixture.
Chill.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned but still soft, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
In saucepan combine chicken, 1/2 salsa, garlic powder, oregano and cumin.
Cook over low heat, stirring until heated through and liquids evaporate.
Brush both sides of flour tortilla with butter.
Spoon 1/6 filling into center of each tortilla.
Fold opposite sides of tortilla inward toward filling. Fold remaining 2 sides over filling to form bundle.

title: peppy pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and allow to cool. Mix together vegetables, sauce, mayonnaise, onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Add pasta. Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Cream margarine or butter and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs and dry ingredients with sour cream.
Add vanilla and coconut; pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mushroom pie
directions: Make pie crust.
Put in a 9-inch plate.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Take off heat.
Add mushrooms and cheese, mixing well.
Put in pie crust.
Make lattice pie crust on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until crust is done.
Serve warm as a side dish with a roast.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In a large saucepan heat milk.
Add rice and simmer 15 minutes.
In a bowl beat egg, sugar, vanilla and evaporated milk. Stir rice, one tablespoon at a time, into the egg mixture.
Return to heat and cook slowly until thick.

title: uncle buck's beef or venison jerky
directions: Slice lean meat to desired thickness.
Put in glass pan and cover with marinade.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Remove from marinade and pat dry with a paper towel.
Lay across oven racks for 3 to 4 hours at 150°.

title: apple-pecan pound cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs in mixer bowl; mix well.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together in bowl.
Add to batter alternately, with pie filling, mixing well after each addition. Stir in pecans.
Spoon into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Take a spattering of freckles across a little nose; add a pair of well-scuffed shoes, some patched and muddy clothes.
Mix in a sandy crew cut, eyes of laughing blue, sunburned cheeks, a toothless smile, grinning up at you.
Then stir in cuts and bruises, a pocketful of stones and add a large capacity for lollipops and cones!
Measure shouts and laughter; add feet that can't be still.
Tend the mixture well and watch with loving care until....at last the precious mixture is finished and you can be sure that restless little boy will be a fine young man!

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix eggs and milk together.
Cook in top of double boiler until mixture begins to thicken. Add sifted flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fried zucchini and cheese
directions: Mix thoroughly and drop well-rounded teaspoons of mixture into hot oil.
Cook until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: corn chowder
directions: Brown bacon; add onions until soft and add diced potatoes. Add water to cover; add seasonings.
Cook until tender, then add corn (with juice), butter and milk or cream.
Heat slowly; do not boil.
Can add 4 ounce can clam with juice.

title: easy coconut custard pie
directions: Blend in blender for 1/2 minute.
Pour into deep 9-inch pie plate, buttered.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until custard is set.

title: tuna puffs
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Add Minute rice.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
(Or cook white or brown rice your favorite way.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash; add onion.
Cook until tender.
Drain off water. Mix together with rest of ingredients.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix or toasted bread crumbs.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Combine eggs, half and half, vanilla, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Trim crust from bread.
Dig into egg mixture.

title: best pumpkin pie
directions: Make pie dough enough for 2 or 3 pies. Put wide strips of dough into rectangle pan. Add about 2 quarts berries or enough to fill pan an inch deep. Put on sugar, enough to sweeten, about 1 1/2 cups (this varies). Put more dough strips on top or solid dough to cover.
Sprinkle a little sugar on top of dough. Bake at 380° for about 1 hour or until browned.

title: strawberry whip
directions: Let Cool Whip and strawberries set at room temperature until soft.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook rice and broccoli according to package directions.
Line baking dish with rice.
Mix broccoli with vegetables.
Add soups and cheese.
Pour over rice and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except stuffing.
Place in well greased 8 x 13-inch or 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
I parboil chicken until easy to pull off bone and cut in small cubes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Use four packs of biscuits; cut each one into 4 with scissors and/or knife.
Roll biscuits in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Toss into a greased Bundt pan.
Boil sugar, butter and water 2 to 3 minutes; pour over cut biscuits.
Bake at 350° for full 30 to 35 minutes.

title: butterflied shrimp in wine
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, mix vermouth, bouillon, pepper, water and salt in a measuring cup and set aside.
Butterfly shrimp; remove shells and devein.
Cut each shrimp 3/4 of the way through, along center back; spread each shrimp open.
In flat saucer, beat egg.
Measure flour into another saucer.
Dip shrimp in egg, then coat with flour.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, heat butter or margarine and salad oil until hot and bubbly. Cook shrimp until lightly browned on both sides (about 1 to 2 minutes per side).
Remove shrimp as they brown.
Return all shrimp to skillet; stir in vermouth mixture.
Over medium-high heat, heat to boiling; cook about 1 minute to blend flavors, stirring occasionally.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: You may have less brisket, but still use 1/2 cup water.
Place the brisket on a sheet of heavy-duty foil.
Add water.
Fold the foil across the top and sides to seal.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours. Drain drippings; refrigerate overnight.
Slice meat cross-grain in thin slices.
Add barbecue sauce between slices, and a small amount on top.
Wrap in foil and heat at 250° for 1 hour.
Drain this sauce off and serve hot with fresh sauce.

title: shrimp-cucumber salad
directions: Blend sugar, poppy seed, salt, mayonnaise, vinegar and parsley together.
Pour over shrimp, cucumber and onion.
Chill at least one hour.
Serve over lettuce leaves.

title: beth's suisse chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Put Swiss cheese on top.
Mix wine and soup and pour over chicken.
Top with crushed croutons and drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: luscious parsnip soup
directions: In large, heavy saucepan, melt butter, then stir in parsnips and celery.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 10 minutes, stirring several times.
Place cooked vegetables in a blender with the flour, parsley and white pepper.
Add 3 cups of broth and blend at high speed.
Return to saucepan and whisk in remaining broth.
Simmer over low heat a few more minutes.
Salt to taste. At serving time, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salamagundi
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Season meat and add tomato sauce, gravy and picante sauce.
Cook together 10 to 15 minutes. Put approximately 1/2 cup of meat mixture in bottom of baking dish.
Fill flour tortillas with about 2 tablespoons of meat mixture and top with shredded cheese.
Fold the filled tortillas in thirds and place in the prepared pan.
Pour remaining meat mixture over tortillas; top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: favorite potato casserole
directions: Combine 1/2 cup margarine, potatoes, sour cream, soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper in large bowl; mix well.
Spoon into greased shallow 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix cornflakes with remaining 1/2 cup margarine in bowl.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: my sister's casserole
directions: The steak (any kind) should be frozen and sliced in thin strips.
Flour the strips and brown in 1 tablespoon of oleo along with the sliced onion.
When brown, add 1 or 2 cups water and the bouillon cube and simmer.
Cook the rice in 1 cup water and 1 teaspoon oleo.
Set aside.
Stir-fry the vegetables and add about 1 teaspoon soy sauce.
Put in bowl:
rice, steak mix and vegetables on top.

title: harvard beets
directions: Save 1/2 of liquid. Heat beets, sugar and vinegar. Add flour to remaining liquid and blend. Pour over beets and cook to desired thickness.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix meal, egg, buttermilk, soda, salt and sugar.
Melt butter in pan.
When hot, pour batter into pan.
Bake at 400° until done (set).

title: easy strawberry frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, salt and strawberries in double boiler.
Place over boiling water.
Beat with electric mixer for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Beat for 5 minutes or until of spreading consistency.
Frost cooled cake.
Enough for 2 layers.

title: summertime cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix angel food cake and break into little pieces with 1 container Cool Whip; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix well and form into 2 loaves.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Put 1/2 cup water in pan.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream brown and white sugars, butter and oil together in large bowl.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk; stir well to mix. Measure flour, spices, salt, baking soda and cocoa into sifter, then sift into bowl.
Grate zucchini into the bowl. Stir until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients on medium-low heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla flavoring.
Stir well.
In glass or metal pan, alternate layers of vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding. For topping, beat egg whites, adding 4 tablespoons sugar very slowly until egg whites form soft peaks.
Spread on pudding.
Bake at 400° until egg whites brown on peaks.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in 9x13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips over coconut.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over butterscotch chips.
Pour the can of milk over the top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: tomato bread
directions: Heat juice and butter together until butter melts.
Add sugar, salt, herbs, ketchup and cheese.
Let cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast on warm water and
stir.
Add
tomato mix and 3 cups of flour to yeast.
Beat
with
electric
mixer at medium for 2 minutes until smooth.
Mix
in enough of remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Knead
by
hand
or
machine
to
10 minutes. Place in greased bowl.
Cover
and
let
rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Punch down and
divide
in half.
Place in greased loaf pans. Cover and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
While still
hot,
brush
top
with oil and cool.

title: easy prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Add flour and spices.
Add prunes and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until thoroughly moist.
Do not overmix. Turn onto floured board and knead 8 to 10 times.
Place on buttered pie plate and bake for 55 minutes in 400° oven.

title: bonbons
directions: Combine dates, nuts and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Shape into balls using 1/2 teaspoon measure.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Add sugar gradually; beat until mixture holds firm peaks. Add vanilla and blend.
Divide meringue in half, tint half red, half green.
Cover date balls with meringue.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Swirl top.
Bake at 250° for about 30 minutes.

title: beef roulade
directions: Spread steaks with mustard, salt and pepper.
Spread onion, bacon, pickle and green pepper on steaks.
Roll as for jelly roll, folding in sides so filling will not fall out.
Tie well with white thread.
Brown quickly in margarine.

Add 1 cup water and cover. As water evaporates, add 1 cup water and cook until meat is tender. Remove the thread from the meat and transfer to a warm platter. Put 2 cups water in the pan and bring to a boil.
Mix thickening of cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Add to boiling water for gravy.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover all the meat and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Set oven to lowest temperature.
Stick toothpick through ends of meat and hang on oven racks.
Place foil under meat to catch drippings.
Bake 4 to 6 hours.

title: fresh corn salad
directions: Place corn in a large saucepan and cover with water; bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes or until tender.
Drain, cool and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix the oil, vinegar, lemon juice, parsley, sugar, salt, basil and cayenne.
Cut cooled corn off the cob.
Add corn, tomatoes, onion and peppers to the oil mixture. Mix well.
Cover and chill for several hours or overnight.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients, adding only enough mayonnaise to hold salad together.
Serve on lettuce leaf and sprinkle with paprika. Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandma archiere's egg casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Butter bread slices on both sides. Fry sausage meat and place over bread in a casserole dish.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over sausage meat.
Beat 6 eggs with salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add bananas and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda 3 times.
Blend wet and dry ingredients. Grease pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Heat margarine on low heat.
Blend flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Stir in broth and milk; bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Pour into pie shell and cover with another pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is brown.

title: quick bread honey-nut coffee cake
directions: Put butter, honey and nuts in pie pan. Set pan in oven until butter melts (this can be done while oven is heating).
Remove from oven. Arrange biscuits on top of mixture. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Remove pan.
Serve hot with butter.
Preparation time:
25 minutes.

title: chicken paprikansh
directions: Cover bottom of a heavy kettle with onions. Brown onions in oil. Cover with Hungarian sweet paprika to make it dark red.
Add red cayenne pepper or dried hot pepper flakes.
Mix and once onions are completely browned, begin with biggest pieces of chicken, fat side down. Salt and pepper each layer.
Add 1 cup water after it is cooking well.
Cover and cook over low heat until chicken is ready to fall off the bones (1 1/2 to 2 hours). Pour off the broth into another pan.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add orange juice.
Add the fruit to the jello.
Let set until firm.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Place rhubarb in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with 1 cup sugar.
Place in oven at 350° while getting mixture ready. Combine butter and remaining sugar.
Sift flour and
soda; blend until crumbly.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Top rhubarb with crumb mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: almost fat-free brownies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed until fluffy; gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add egg whites, sour cream,
milk and vanilla. Beat well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients.
Stir well. Add flor mixture to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Frost.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix above ingredients (except chocolate morsels) with mixer until mixed well. Stir in chocolate morsels by hand and pour into Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the pork roast, in a large plastic bag.
Place roast in, press all the air out and tie securely.
Marinate for 2 hours or longer. Reserve the marinade. Place roast on a rack in shallow roasting pan.
Pour half of the marinade into roaster.
Roast at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Baste with remaining marinade every 20 minutes.
Refrigerate any leftover meat in the marinade.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream, mushroom soup and garlic together and pour over green beans.
In saucepan or microwave dish, melt margarine and add enough crushed crackers to absorb margarine.
Spread over green bean mixture.
Sprinkle shredded Colby cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice with water to make a cup. Bring to boil. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved. Stir in ice cubes and cold water to make a cup. Chill until thickened. Add all other ingredients. Stir and chill.

title: microwave chocolate apples
directions: You will need sticks (bamboo skewers will do).

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix together the yogurt and Cool Whip, then mash the partially thawed fruit and blend into the yogurt mixture.
Pour in pie crust.
Place in freezer for one hour or until frozen.
Thaw 1/2 hour prior to serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside other half of batter.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: basic white sauce
directions: In a saucepan combine cornstarch and milk.
Add salt and butter.
Stir constantly until slightly thick.
Remove from heat and continue to stir as it will cook a little more.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell (deep dish).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: susan's low-fat trifle
directions: Place pieces of angel food cake in bottom of glass trifle bowl.
Place slices of fresh fruit in layers.
Sprinkle with sugar substitute.
Spread low-fat strawberry yogurt.
Repeat these steps.
Top with no-fat whipped cream.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Put roast in pan. Place onion on top. Mix all other ingredients together and pour over top of roast. Cover and bake at 300° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Combine well beaten egg and milk; mix with butter and sugar mixture.
Sift or stir together with fork the dry ingredients.
Gradually blend dry ingredients to mixture.
Fold in oats, raisins and chopped pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: hello dollies
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter.
Add crackers.
Pour over milk.
Add chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender in a quart of water; do not pour out water!
Remove bones and skin and tear meat apart.
Add all ingredients except biscuits.
Roll biscuits out and cut in thin strips.
Drop in pot with chicken.
Cook for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken-fried steaks
directions: Pour enough cooking oil into a skillet to measure about 1/2-inch deep. Heat oil on medium-high until hot.

title: wanda's salsa
directions: Wash tomatoes; dip in boiling water for 1/2 minute to loosen skin.
Dip into cold water; drain.
Core, peel and quarter tomatoes and remove seeds if you want to (I didn't).
Chop into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
In separate pan, melt cheese with tomatoes (including juice).
Add soup and chicken and simmer.
Drain spaghetti and add all ingredients.
Cook over low heat until hot.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: In a large glass bowl, melt almond bark in microwave.
Stir in peanut butter, marshmallows and Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Cool.

title: sausage delights
directions: Have sausage and cheese at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls and bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 100 sausage balls.
These balls may be baked, frozen and reheated for surprise company.

title: coffee coke float
directions: Half-fill 2 tall glasses with chilled coffee.
Stir in cream. Add a scoop of ice cream to each glass and top with Coca-Cola. Serves 2.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Skin the chicken and place skins in water to boil.
Lay breasts flat and put 1 slice of the cheese on them and then a little of the shaved ham.
Roll the breasts up with the cheese and ham in the middle.
Roll these in the stuffing and place in casserole pan.

Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until done. After boiling the skins, remove the skins and use about 1 cup of the broth with cream of chicken soup and white wine for sauce to go over the cooked breasts.
This can be served as a gravy to accompany the breasts.

title: trail mix
directions: Measure each ingredient into a big bowl and stir them together with a big spoon. Package in 4 separate bags and eat outdoors with your camping buddies.

title: orange muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 muffin cups with Pam, or line with paper liners.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Grate zest of orange and juice it.
Add enough milk to orange juice to measure 1/2 cup, plus 2 tablespoons.
Pour into a second bowl.
Add butter, egg, vanilla and baking soda; whisk until blended.
Add wet ingredients to dry; combine with as few strokes as possible.
Fold in orange zest and pecans.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be glazed with orange juice, zest and sugar.

title: baked fruit
directions: Melt butter and mix with sugar and curry powder.
Pour over fruit that has been placed in a flat baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Use sauce over ice cream or cakes.

title: nut pudding
directions: Let first 3 ingredients come to a boil. Then add gelatine. Cool, then add vanilla, cream and nuts. Put in cold place until set (about 2 to 3 hours).

title: garden herb dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well in food processor or blender.
Pour into serving dish and chill overnight.
Garnish with parsley and serve with Fritos or crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Heat peas and soup; add diced cheese.
Pour into casserole dish; bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Mix cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: beef stroganoff(grandma's recipe)
directions: Trim fat from beef; cut fillet crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Cut each slice across grain into 1/2-inch wide strips (about 2 inches long).
Slowly heat large, heavy skillet.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Add beef strips, just enough to cover skillet bottom.
Over high heat, sear quickly on all sides.
Remove with tongs as meat finishes browning (it should be brown on outside and rare inside).
In 3 tablespoons hot butter in same skillet, saute onion, garlic and mushrooms until onion is golden (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add flour, meat extract paste, catsup, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually add bouillon.
Bring it to a boil, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Spoon into muffin tins, about half full.
Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes.
Makes 6.

title: broccoli tuna roll ups
directions: Mix soup and milk; set aside.
Mix tuna,1/2 c. cheese, broccoli, 1/2 can onions and 1/2 of the soup mixture.
Place mixture on tortillas and roll.
Place seam side down in lightly greased baking dish.
Pour remaining soup over top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 c. grated cheese and 1/2 can french fried onions.
Bake uncovered, 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rye bread, 1 day before serving.
Serve with rye bread.

title: organic bread
directions: Mix yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add oatmeal, honey and milk; mix well.
Stir in white flour.
Let rise 45 to 60 minutes.
Stir in eggs, salt and cooking oil.
Work in wheat flour and wheat germ.
Let rise double; knead 5 minutes.
Divide into 2 loaves. Place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Cover with clean cloth; let rise in warm place until double again.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Remove from pans to cool.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onion until light and brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until rice is tender, about 30 minutes.
(Add small amount of water during cooking if necessary.)

title: yummy no-fail pecan pie
directions: *Or purchase in dairy section of store.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells; rinse and set aside.
Squeeze spinach (cooked). Combine with Ricotta, Parmesan, eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg. Stuff shells with mixture.
Place 1/2 of sauce in pan; put shells, open side up, in a row.
Spoon remaining sauce over shells.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and broil for 5 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Drop carrots in boiling salted water; cook until crispy tender.
Drain in cold water; add all vegetables and other ingredients to bowl.
Cover tightly.
Let stand overnight so flavors mix.
Will keep indefinitely refrigerated and tightly covered.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and put in crock-pot.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add olive oil.
Add shrimp and garlic and saute until shrimp is pink.
Add capers, parsley, oregano, lemon juice, salt and peppers.
Cook for approximately 2 minutes more.

title: corn relish
directions: Put corn in boiling water; boil 3 minutes and dip in cold water.
Cut off cob, combine corn with all ingredients and boil 15 minutes.
Pack into jars.
Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook parsley, onions, garlic and ground chuck until meat is brown.
Add tomato sauce and paste, Worcestershire sauce, salt and oregano and simmer for 1 hour.
In 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish, arrange in layer the noodles, sauce and cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: cream cheese pastries
directions: Blend egg yolk, sugar and cream cheese.
Press 1 tube crescent roll dough into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cheese mixture over dough, then lightly lay 1 tube of crescent rolls dough on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While pastry is warm, drizzle glaze on top.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk; blend well.
Cook uncovered over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Reduce heat and continue to cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Spread small amount on bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with layer of wafers.
Top with layer of bananas.
Pour about 1/3 of custard over bananas. Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard to make 3 layers of each, ending with custard.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not too dry.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Spoon on top of pudding, spreading to cover entire surface and sealing well to edges.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until slightly brown.
Chill; garnish with bananas and wafers.
Serves 8.

title: may's louisiana strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch (heaped) with water.
Using thick pot, cook mix until very thick consistency, then remove from heat. Stir in 3 tablespoons strawberry jello. Cool.
May add 3 to 4 drops red food coloring to mix.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cups bite size halved strawberries.
Put into
9-inch baked and cooled pie crust. Chill pie and top with Cool Whip or whipping cream to serve.
May make double recipe.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt morsels, peanut butter and oil.
Use 2 cups cereal; pour morsels, peanut butter and oil over cereal.
Coat with 10x sugar. Serve.

title: lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon 3 inches apart on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are browned.
Yields about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: ranch-style chicken
directions: Clean and flour chicken.
Melt one stick of butter in open pan.
Brown chicken in "open" pan.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and milk in bowl.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan and pour soup mixture over it.
Cook at 350° for one hour (covered pan).
Twenty minutes before it is done, pour peaches with juice over chicken, cover and finish cooking.
Serve with rice and vegetables.

title: apple crumb
directions: Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar, dash of cinnamon and 1/2 cup water.
Makes crumbs of.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all together.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: "mari"nated noodles and cabbage(salad)
directions: Break up noodles.
In a mixing bowl, combine oil, vinegar, sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper and seasoning packet from noodle mix.
Stir to dissolve seasonings.
Stir in broken noodles, cabbage, chicken, onion and sesame seed.
Cover and chill several hours.
Before serving, stir in almonds.
Garnish with pepper slices. Serves 6 to 8.

title: teriyaki pineapple pork chops
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, combine brown sugar, soy sauce, garlic powder and reserved pineapple juice; mix well. Place pork chops in marinade, turning to coat all sides. cover and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours, turning chops once. When ready to barbecue, drain pork chops. Reserve marinade. Place pork chops on grill 4 to 6-inches from medium-high coals. Cook 20 to 30 minutes or until fork tender and no longer pink, turning once and brushing frequently with marinade.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
In broth, add dumplings and a few drops of yellow food coloring.
While chicken cooks, cook the mixture of vegetables, chopped small.
When vegetables are tender and dumplings are done, add it all together and serve.
To the chicken bouillon, add 1 cup milk and flour to thicken before you drop in dumplings.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Use garlic or onion powder if cheese tastes too salty.

title: lemonade pies
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie crusts.
Freeze pies.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes prior to serving.

title: ray's salsa
directions: Put garlic and jalapeno peppers in blender with juice from 2 cans whole tomatoes.
Blend briefly!
Do not blend to a puree. Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and cilantro.
Blend briefly.
Add onion.
Blend very briefly.
Chop up whole tomatoes in can with knife.
Add tomatoes to blender.
Add 1 large tablespoon of parsley to blender.
Add black pepper to taste (optional).
Blend for 50 milliseconds (less than a second).
Serve with nacho chips.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion, pepper and tomatoes.
Let cook about 3 minutes.
Add spaghetti pieces.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with Cheddar cheese and return to oven to melt cheese.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Combine all ingredients in large soup kettle with
3 quarts water.
Bring to a boil and simmer, uncovered, for two hours or until black-eyed peas are tender.
Drain; remove whole bay leaves, garlic, peppercorns and ham bone.
Remove ham from bone; chop and add back to beans.
Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: classic walforf salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Add 1 large container of Cool Whip.

title: just meat loaf
directions: Top with catsup before baking.
Combine ingredients, bake in greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove grease with baster as loaf bakes.

title: apple coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil, then add eggs one at a time; beat.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to first mixture.
Add vanilla, apples, nuts and coconut.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: laura's corn
directions: Cook corn. When done, cut off cob. Add scallions, garlic and tomato. Cook rice. When done, salt and pepper to taste. Add chicken broth and add all other ingredients. Good with chicken.

title: fried dried apple pies
directions: Put water and apples in a 3-quart saucepan and cook on medium high heat until apples are falling apart.
Add more water, if needed, but don't leave very juicy.
Mash apples.
Mix spices and sugar; add to apples.
Set aside to cool.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix vegetables; cook for 20 minutes, until they are mushy. Add 1 cup of milk and sour cream.

title: rocky road pizza
directions: Turn oven on to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter with mixer on medium until softened.
Add sugar and brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: souper burgers
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet; drain.
Add cream of onion soup and small amount of water to mix to consistency of Sloppy Joes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: graham cracker pineapple pudding
directions: Cook together in saucepan, stirring constantly.
When it thickens, add the crushed pineapple (with juice) and cook through. Put graham crackers and pineapple pudding in alternate layers in a baking dish, starting with crackers on bottom of dish.
Top with beaten egg whites and brown in oven.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream your butter, peanut butter and your vanilla.
Add the sugar and work it real good with hands.
Form into balls.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together; pour into a greased skillet and bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon oatmeal bars
directions: Mix milk, juice and rind.
Let it sit.
Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and oats.
Pat flat 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour lemon mix over top.
Add salt to remaining crust mix.
Cover with remaining oatmeal mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cook for 15 minutes on rack.
Cut when cool.
Then cover and store in refrigerator.

title: fresh orange cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Cool to room temperature. Combine cake mix and oil; beat in eggs, one at a time. Add orange extract. Mix well. Add salt and dissolved gelatin. Beat for 3 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tester comes out clean. Remove from oven and immediately pour mixture of confectioners sugar dissolved in orange juice over top of cake. Cool cake in pan for at least half a day. Even better if covered and refrigerated for 24 hours. Serves 8 to 10.

title: veggie mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; let cool a few minutes, then blend into the cheese.
Add mayo and seasonings, beating until smooth.
Add green pepper, onion and cucumber.
Spoon into an oiled mold and chill.
Excellent with ham.

title: tomatoes nicoise
directions: Heat 2 Tbsp. olive oil.
Add garlic & onion.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Spread this mixture evenly in a 9 x 13 inch glass baking dish.
Top with sliced tomatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle on top.
Drizzle with 2 Tbsp. olive oil.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour, egg and juice.
Cook until thick.
Pour over pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill before serving.

title: blueberry pudding cake
directions: Put blueberries in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, shortening, 3/4 cup sugar and milk together. Spread over berries.

title: flour tortillas and sopaipillas
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut lard in. Add hot water in small amounts while kneading thoroughly. Dough should be stiff and not sticky.

title: turkey meatballs
directions: Mix jelly, ketchup and lemon juice in a medium size pan.
Heat until it bubbles.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients and beat well.
Stir in finely chopped zucchini.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 325° or until springs back when lightly touched.

title: tangy hot sauce for meat and chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Stir in tuna and celery.
Mix well. Form into 3 balls and chill several hours on wax paper.
Combine nuts and parsley and roll each tuna ball in mixture.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Blend in flour and nuts.
(May need to work this dough by hand to mix completely.)
Shape in balls or crescent shapes.
Bake at 325° on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes.
When cookies are completely cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Mix pudding and gelatin.
Cook with a little more milk than pudding recipe calls for.
Cool.
Cream sugar and peanut butter together, gradually add milk to make a thin paste.
Add vanilla, salt, and pudding and rest of milk to almost the fill line.

title: sweet sour baked beans
directions: Place onion rings in skillet.
Add sugar, mustard, garlic, salt and vinegar.
Cook, covered, 20 minutes.
Add to combined beans in 3 quart baking dish.
Add bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: corn-bean casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour in dish. Sprinkle with cheese and almonds on top.
Melt margarine.
Mix with crackers and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and margarine together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with hot milk and vanilla.
It is enough for one (9 x 13-inch) or 4-layer cake.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine.
Add chips and peanut butter.
Put cereal into oblong cake pan and pour mixture over cereal.
Mix well to coat all cereal.
Dump mixture into grocery bag with powdered sugar and shake until well coated.
Put in freezer for 2 hours to set up or in refrigerator all day or overnight.
Store in airtight container.

title: old fashion prune cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add other ingredients in order, beating well after each one.
Pour into buttered pan, 11 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° until cake is done in middle but soft to the touch, about 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: mom's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Use a number 8 cast-iron pan.
Melt brown sugar and butter. Mix all other ingredients well (except pineapple and cherries). Place pineapple in pan.
Pour batter onto top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes to cool.
Flip onto plate and place cherries in center of pineapple.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg until fluffy.
Add chopped apples, flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, soda and salt.
Mix well. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased and lightly floured baking pan. Combine brown sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nuts; sprinkle over batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sutene revol argentinian style(elegant and tasty as well as easy to make)
directions: Cut the onion in fourths.
Salt the meat; take the fat off. Brown the meat with a little olive oil at a high temperature.
Add the onions, bay leaves and rosemary; cook 1 minute.
Add the beer. Let it boil and turn the temperature to low/simmer.
Cover the pot with a lid and let it cook for 1 1/2 hours.
The meat will be overcooked.

title: imitation blintzes
directions: Cut crust of bread and roll each piece flat with a rolling pin. Spread each piece with layer of cream cheese.
Roll each piece up and cut in half.
Dip each in melted butter or margarine.
Then roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight, then bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 1/2 quart casserole.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, add beans, drain on paper towels and chill well.
Combine with greens, tomatoes and cheese and toss with dressings.
The buttermilk style dressing should be mixed according to directions on the package, reducing the buttermilk to 1/4 cup.
Add taco sauce if desired and just before serving add crumbled tortilla chips.
Serve with additional chips.

title: jamaican avocado dip
directions: Halve the avocados and scoop out all the flesh.
Either put all the ingredients in a blender or press the avocados through a sieve to get it very smooth. If using ham, omit salt. Add other ingredients.
Serve dip with crackers.
Serves 6.

title: mom's whipped cream icing
directions: Boil until thick flour and milk.
Let set until cold.
Cream together oleo and sugar.
Beat in milk mixture.
Covers 1 (8-inch) cake.

title: peach allspice jam
directions: Prepare 5 (1/2-pint) freezer jars according to manufacturer's instructions.
Chop peaches to make 4 cups.
Place peaches in strainer over glass measuring cup to drain juice and add enough apple juice to make 1 cup total.
Combine juice and allspice in medium saucepan; add pectin slowly, stirring constantly to prevent lumps.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat, stirring constantly to avoid scorching.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir in peaches, sweetener and lemon juice.
Fill freezer jars to within 1/2-inch of top.
Wipe jar rims; cover with lids. Let stand at room temperature 4 hours.
Refrigerate until chilled or place jam in freezer.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into a large bowl.
Melt marshmallows and water.
In a saucepan, bring sugar and evaporated milk to a boil.
Boil slowly for 6 minutes.
Stir often.
Pour sugar and milk over nuts, chips, etc. and stir until all is melted.
Pour melted marshmallows into mixture and mix well.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm and cut.

title: ham ball(club member: laine)
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, grated ham, chopped parsley, onion, dry mustard, onion and pepper sauce. Form into ball. Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in bowl.
Add crabmeat (drained) and break meat apart gently with fork.
Toss gently to mix with dry ingredients.
Start heating the frypan on low heat.
Add the mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, egg and mustard and toss very gently, being careful not to break up the meat, but mix well. Form into 6 cakes.

title: blueberry supper bread
directions: Prepare batter from muffin mix according to package directions for coffeecake or loaf cake.
Pour into a greased 8 1/2-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle with Crumb Top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cut in wedges to serve.
Serve warm with plenty of butter.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: best beef marinade
directions: Combine all.
Marinate steaks, London broil, etc., overnight. Grill as usual.

title: apricot hornes
directions: Blend ingredients together with hands.
Add more flour if needed.
Shape into 1-inch balls and refrigerate overnight.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg into bowl.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain fat and set aside.
In large pot, add onion, garlic and oil.
Saute until tender.
Add the meat with the chili powder, cumin, salt, Worcestershire, tomatoes, green pepper, tomato sauce and kidney beans.
Simmer at least 2 hours. This is better the second day.

title: vanilla chip chocolate cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla extract; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir together the flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually blend into butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla milk chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)
Cool slightly; remove to wire rack. Cool completely.
Yields about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: sausage balls
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix together well. Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
These may be made in advance and frozen before cooking.

title: dot's brown bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and let stand overnight.
Add rest of ingredients, blending well, and bake in 6 (1 pound) greased coffee cans for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in cans.

title: veggie finger sandwiches
directions: Blend and drain the carrots, cucumbers, bell pepper and onion. Mix all together and spread on fresh bread; cut away brown edges. Cut into little squares.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring water, sugar and coffee to a boil.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in brandy, vodka and vanilla.
Put in bottle and let set a few days.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread apart into small pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Set aside.
Brown and drain sausage; crumble and spoon over bread pieces.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and salt; mix well and pour over sausage and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Yields 10 servings.

title: easy lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in pineapple until it reaches boiling point. Cool until it starts to jell, then add other ingredients.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts, if desired.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower 10 minutes and drain. Saute green pepper in butter until tender. Add flour and stir in milk. Cook until thickened. Add salt and dash of pepper and mushrooms. Place cauliflower in casserole dish, cover with cheese slices then in 350 degree oven.

title: pizza pasta
directions: In large skillet, brown pepperoni; drain.
Add green pepper, onion, mushrooms, olives and garlic; saute.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, tomato paste and oil; blend well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add cooked mostaccioli; blend well.
Pour in 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole; top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger mincemeat
directions: Cook meat until red color is gone.
Separate into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Seal tight.
Store in refrigerator.
Use for pies or cookies.

title: brownies
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add the chocolate syrup and flour, then nuts.
Pour batter into a lightly buttered jelly roll pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: victoria fudge
directions: Cook sugar and cream together to form a soft ball.
Add butter.
Cool to room temperature, 110°.
Beat until almost creamy.
Add coconut, fruits, nuts and flavoring.
Pour into a shallow, well buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, onions and oil until onions turn clear (5 to 10 minutes).
Add soup and milk and bring to a boil.
Add rice, 1 cup of cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish and top with remaining cup of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rivel soup
directions: Mix with fork the flour, salt and 1 egg to form rivels. Boil milk; add rivels.
Boil until done, a few minutes.
Can add potatoes or parsley.

title: chocolate banana cream pie(diabetic)
directions: Cut up bananas into pie crust.
Mix pudding, milk powder, water, 1/4 of the whipped topping and 3/4 teaspoon of coconut extract together.
Should be runny.
Pour over bananas.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from bones.
Heat soup.
Do not boil. Mix chicken, mayonnaise, celery, onion and soup.
Put in greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Put dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crescent turnover
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain fat.
Stir in barbecue sauce. Roll out crescent rolls in 4 strips making a rectangle on a cookie sheet.
Spread meat down the middle (about 4 inches wide).
Top with cheese slices.
Fold dough over the top and pinch shut. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Add all vegetables first to a crock-pot, then slowly add liquids.
Cook on low for 5 hours.
Serve warm.
Yields 8 servings, one hour to prepare.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Stir until sugar melts.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: brandenburg peanut butter pie
directions: Mix eggs, corn syrup,
sugar, peanut butter and vanilla together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until top is
brown
and
crisp.
Serve with ice cream if desired.

title: fresh summer blueberry pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and put in pie shell and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Combine last 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir and melt.
Pour over pie and bake for 10 more minutes.
This is wonderful and easy!

title: okra with tomato sauce
directions: Wash okra. Cut off stems and slice.
Brown onion in butter, add okra and cook 3 minutes.
Place in baking dish, season.
Pour tomato sauce over it.
Sprinkle with parsley and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Excellent with chicken dishes. Serves 6.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla, eggs and milk.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Mix dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Chill dough 2 to 3 hours or use immediately.
Roll on floured surface.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.
Great for making children's cutout cookies.

title: peach pie
directions: Line unbaked deep pie shell with sliced peaches.
Mix butter, sugar, flour and egg.
Pour over sliced peaches.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Top with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well.
To serve, use 2 teaspoons per cup, adding boiling water.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients together and mix into batter.
Add vanilla and fold in apples last.
Bake in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish for 45 minutes at 375°.
Cut in squares and serve warm.
(Keeps well.)

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Sift 1/4 cup sugar, flour and cocoa together in a small bowl; set aside.
Beat egg whites in an extra large bowl at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and the next 3 ingredients; beat until soft peaks form.
Gradually add remaining 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Sift flour mixture over egg white mixture, 1/4 cup at a time, folding in carefully after each addition.
Spoon batter into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan; spread evenly with a spatula.
Break large air pockets by cutting through batter with a knife.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt margarine in pan and add sugar.
Combine milk, egg yolks, flour and vanilla; add to first mixture.
Stir until thick and boil 3 minutes.
Pour in prepared pie shell.
To make meringue, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until it forms peaks.
Put on pie and brown in oven.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in blender for 30 seconds.
Makes 6 cups.

title: aunt sarah's pumpkin spice cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, pumpkin and oil; blend in nuts.
Grease and flour cake pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated carrots or "copper pennies"
directions: Combine in Tupperware container and refrigerate.
Lasts for days.

title: peach-pineapple frozen delite
directions: Mix, place in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, Cheez Whiz and soup together. Add celery, onion and broccoli.
Pour all ingredients into a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish. Dot with butter (optional).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set.
Garnish with fresh fruit if desired.

title: salsa picante
directions: Chop all of the ingredients and simmer together over low heat for 2 hours.
Freeze in bags.
This is very good and you do not have to can it in jars!

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine first seven ingredients and cook until thickened. Brown butter until golden brown and add to mixture.
Put crumbled Favorite Pralines in bottom of baked pie crust and pour cooled filling over pralines.
Cover filling with Superior Meringue and bake at 350° until meringue is brown, about 30 minutes.

title: scones
directions: Mix all together. Bake for 20 to 40 minutes.

title: apple slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Soften tortillas in oil; drain.
Layer in square baking dish. Place 3 tortillas, cheese, onion, beef and top with a sauce made from mixing the enchilada sauce, taco sauce and the cream of chicken soup.
Continue in layers until you have 4 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Shred lettuce. Serve casserole over shredded lettuce.

title: strawberry jam coffee cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and oleo.
Stir in Bisquick until mixture is crumbly.
Add milk.
Turn out on floured surface and roll around, adding a little flour or Bisquick until dough is not sticky.
Roll dough into an 8 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread jam down center of dough.
Using scissors or sharp knife, cut 2 inches into dough toward center, at 1 inch intervals on each side of the dough (you should have 11 cuts or 12 strips on each side of dough).
Braid strips by crisscrossing alternately from side to side.
Seal strips in the middle.
Carefully place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Drizzle with simple icing while warm.

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; soak 2 hours in ice water.
Heat vinegar and sugar but don't boil.
Set off stove and cool.
Drain cucumbers and pour cooled syrup over.
Set for 1 hour and then freeze.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, stirring lightly.
Drop a teaspoon of batter for each hush puppy into 360° hot deep fat, frying only a few at a time.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine water and margarine in saucepan.
Heat over medium heat and bring to rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add flour; heat and stir until mixture forms a ball.
Turn mixture into a bowl and beat 1 minute to cool.
Add eggs and beat 4 minutes. Drop dough by tablespoons 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Turn oven down to 375° and bake 15 minutes more. Turn off heat.
Make small slits in sides and return to oven 10 minutes, leaving door ajar.
Fill with bananas and whipping cream or yogurt.

title: maui onion soup
directions: Saute 1 pound Maui or sweet onions, thinly sliced, in 1/4 pound butter until golden brown.
Add red wine, bay leaf and beef stock. Bring to boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Pour into 4 ovenproof soup bowls.
Place 1 thin slice of toasted French bread on top and cover with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.
Place in oven and broil until bubbly and browned.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add margarine, beaten eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into
unbaked pie crust.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: ferroll's chicken and rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients; place in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in frozen strawberries and add pineapple (including juice).
Slice bananas and place in bottom of mold (9-inch fluted).
Add half of jello mixture to the bananas.
Place in mold in refrigerator.
Put remaining jello mixture in bowl and refrigerate.
When partially set, remove bowl and fold in Cool Whip until mixture is pink.
Spread this pink mixture over banana mixture in mold.
Chill overnight or until firm.
Can be made 2 days ahead.
Serves 15.
This makes pretty salad for Christmas or Valentine's day.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash and pick over beans.
Place in large pot.
Cover with water; bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Cover.
Turn off heat; let stand 1 hour.
Simmer for 1 or 2 hours, until beans are half cooked.
Brown the meat in oil with onion in a large skillet. Add Chili-O mix, garlic, chili powder and basil; mix well.
Stir in tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Cover; allow this to stand for a few hours.
Heat through with the rice when ready to serve.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: peachy pork chops
directions: Place chops in a single layer in a baking dish.
Place peaches on top of chips.
Mix Worcestershire sauce with peach liquid and pour over chops.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: yummy brownies
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 375°. Blend all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Spread mixture in a greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Press lightly.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine 2 parts Chutney with 1 part mayonnaise.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown beef in frying pan. Add onion and celery. Cook until wilted, stirring occasionally.
Add cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Stir until mixed and bubbling. Add pepper. Add rice or pasta. Serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chops and potato casserole
directions: Season and brown pork chops.
Place potatoes and onion in large buttered baking dish.
Place browned chops on top of potatoes and onion.
Mix sour cream, mushroom soup and water; pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: impossible chicken-vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease or Pam pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inch). Mix chicken, vegetables and cheese.
Spoon evenly into pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with wire whisk or hand beater or until smooth.
Pour evenly over chicken.

title: mock bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Have ready a pie plate or six 2/3-cup capacity custard cups.
Put margarine in pie plate to melt.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll into small balls.
Press down with a fork or glass.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Combine all except reserved muffin mix.
Turn into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved muffin mix.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with the bananas, beating well after each addition.
Add nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 70 minutes or until well done.
(Some ovens do not take 70 minutes.)

title: steak 'n bacon
directions: Cut round steak into bite size pieces and wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around steak.
Place a toothpick through steak to hold the bacon on.
In a skillet, add Worcestershire sauce and water; bring to a boil.
Place meat in skillet and add a little salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes on low heat.
Then turn heat up to high to cook off sauce.
Be careful, the sauce will cook off but grease will remain.
Allow meat to brown as desired, then take up from pan.

title: banana split pie
directions: Beat together eggs, margarine and powdered sugar for 15 to 20 minutes.
Slice bananas and layer in bottom of crust.
Place drained pineapple over bananas and pour filling over bananas and pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and decorate with cherries and nuts.

title: graham cracker torte
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; add sugar gradually.
Add remaining ingredients and fold until thoroughly mixed.
Bake in greased pan in moderate oven (325°) about 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut in squares. Serve with whipped cream or milk.

title: baked corn
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and pour in casserole.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered.

title: raw macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased casserole dish.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave fantastic peanut brittle
directions: Stir together the peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Place in microwave and cook on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla; stir well.
Return to microwave for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove, add soda and stir until foamy.
Pour at once onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Break into pieces and store in an airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: delicious eggs
directions: Bring to a boil the stewed tomatoes. Carefully cut hard-boiled eggs in half lengthwise.
Distribute in tomato sauce.
Sprinkle on top of eggs the ham, onions, olive oil and sweet peas.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Lightly mix in ground beef, then crumbs, onion and pepper.
Add horseradish, salt, mustard, milk and 1/4 cup of catsup; combine lightly but well. Transfer to baking dish and shape into loaf.
Spread remaining catsup on top.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit dip(teacher appreciation week)
directions: In medium bowl, combine ingredients and mix until smooth. Serve with cut up fruit.
Enjoy.

title: a man's delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the boiling water with enough pineapple juice added to make 1 cup. Add marshmallows and heat until they are melted. Cool and beat until frothy. Add remaining ingredients, folding whipped cream in last. Pour into mold or Bundt type pan and chill until firm, usually overnight. Serves 8.

title: homemade salad dressing(especially for potato salad)
directions: Place all in top of double boiler and beat until smooth. Cool thoroughly and put in a glass jar. Refrigerate after cooling and it keeps for several weeks. Good also on macaroni salads.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic.
Put in pan lined with foil. Put rice on top of chicken, then put frozen vegetables on top of them.
Cover with chicken broth.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk, and oleo until it comes to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add in peanut butter and vanilla. Spread into parchment lined 9 x 13 pan and cool.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Boil 2 cups water; pour over Jell-O.
Add crushed pineapple and frozen blueberries; stir well and refrigerate until jelled.
Blend softened cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Spread with spatula on top of Jell-O.
Can add chopped walnuts on top if desired.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Add pineapple, orange and ReaLemon juice.
Chill overnight or 2 or 3 hours.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: mexican layered dip(for corn chips)
directions: Place refried beans in bottom of shallow dish.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning and layer over refried beans.
Sprinkle the top with green onions, olives, chopped tomatoes and grated cheese.

title: tropical fruit pie
directions: Cook pineapple, flour and sugar until slightly thick.
Cut up 1 1/2 bananas in each crust.
Put 1/2 pineapple mixture on top of bananas in each pie.
Add to each pie 1/4 cup nuts on top of pineapple and 1 1/2 cups coconut on top of nuts.
