Cool completely. Top each pie with Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: green corn casserole
directions: Heat corn, milk and salt just to boiling and slowly stir in grits. Cook and stir over medium heat until smooth and thickened, about 5 minutes. Beat in butter, sugar, Swiss cheese and chilies. Beat eggs lightly and stir a little of the hot mixture into them. Stir eggs back into hot grits. Blend until smooth. Turn into a shallow greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese on top. Let stand 30 minutes. Bake at 350° until golden on top, about 1 hour. Serve warm. Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 2 times.
Add other ingredients and stir until evenly mixed.
Raisins, nuts or dates may be added. Pour in 2 well-greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: lemon spice surprise
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Prepare lemon pudding mix (not instant) as directed on package.
Spread in ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inches.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: For each serving, spread salad dressing and salsa on tortilla. Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with lettuce and meat.
Roll up.
Wrap each tortilla in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix ingredients with beater until stiff. Place in crust. Chill 4 hours. Top as desired.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots, orange juice and salt in medium saucepan. Cover and cook over medium heat until crisp and tender.
Stir in orange rind, brown sugar and margarine.
Cook until carrots are glazed.
Toss with parsley and almonds.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant and onion until tender. Drain. Chop finely. Add butter, crumbled bread, half of cheese and egg yolk. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix well. Beat egg white until stiff and fold into mixture. Pour into buttered shallow dish and sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake for 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: punch fantasy
directions: Combine juices and water.
Place sherbet and ice cream on bottom of bowl and break into small pieces with spoon.
Add juices and water.
Stir until sherbet and ice cream are partially melted.
Serves about 30.

title: cheese ball *
directions: Cream the cheese and sharp cheese together.
Mix and cream together the remaining ingredients.
Shape into a large or two small balls.
Chill overnight.
When firm, roll in finely chopped pecans.
Add cherry on top.
Will freeze.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn and remove all unpopped kernels.
In saucepan, combine sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Boil over medium heat until temperature on candy thermometer reaches 330°, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon.
Remove from heat when temperature is 330°. Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over popcorn in large bowl. Stir until corn is well coated.
Spread corn onto counter and cool.
Break apart pieces when completely cool.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients, pack in containers and freeze.

title: taco tray
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients with a mixer.
Spread on a round tray.
Fry 1 pound ground hamburger and add 1/2 package of taco seasoning mix and simmer.
When cool, put on top of spread.
Top with lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Serve with crackers or Doritos.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa on medium heat; boil 5 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter, marshmallow and vanilla thoroughly.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until fork tender; remove from water and drain. Mix soup and sour cream (may use fat free sour cream; it works just as well as the real stuff).

Pull or cut chicken into bite size portions and mix with sour cream and soup mixture. Layer in casserole dish starting with crushed Ritz crackers; then put a layer of chicken mixture, repeat this until all of chicken is used and ending with crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Melt oleo and pour over top and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian sausage soup with tortellini
directions: Remove sausage casing and crumble in large pot.
Add garlic and onion and cook until meat is browned.
Drain off grease.
Add tomatoes, water, fennel and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Drain and add to other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix everything else together.
Pour half of batter in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with nut mixture.
Pour in remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 - 45 minutes

title: brownies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and melted chocolate.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Let cool.
You can frost with chocolate frosting if you'd like.

title: granny casserole
directions: Mix cheeses, sour cream, pepper and onion using mixer while noodles are cooking.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomato sauce. Cook about 8 minutes until not watery.
Butter 2 medium casseroles or 1 large deep casserole.
Put noodles in bottom; cheese layer next; use all (sauce mixture on top).
May sprinkle Parmesan cheese or Mozzarella cheese on top of all.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sunday supper hamburger
directions: Brown onion lightly in butter.
Add ground beef and brown. Combine remaining ingredients, except flakes.
Blend well.
Turn into buttered large baking dish.
Top with flakes.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rice and green chile casserole
directions: Mix rice, salt, sour cream, Monterey Jack cheese and chiles. Place in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Microwave at High for 5 minutes, turning 1/4 turn halfway through cooking or bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot and cheese melts.

title: norwegian almond cookies(norske mandel kaker)
directions: Sift flour, salt and cardamom.
Cream butter and sugar until very light.
Then beat in egg and milk.
Add flour and ground almonds and mix until smooth.
Put into a cookie press and make into shapes desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grandma lossie's cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour into bowl.
Make a well in center and add shortening.
Mix flour and shortening together until mealy.
Add milk gradually to form a soft dough.
Continue to work in rest of flour to form a dough that can be handled.
Knead dough in bowl or on floured board about 3 to 5 times.
Pinch off biscuit size pieces of dough and flatten slightly in the hand.
Put a 1-inch piece of medium sharp Cheddar cheese in center and pull edges up to seal well.
Place sealed edge down on baking sheet. Bake at 450° for about 12 minutes.
Serve hot.
Cheese will be melted inside.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Combine cake mix and coconut.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Lightly press onto bottom and half up sides of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Arrange peaches over crust.
Combine sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle evenly over peaches.
Blend sour cream and egg. Pour over all. Bake at 350° until sour cream sets, about 10 minutes. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water (cover pan) until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain well.
Combine oil, vinegar and black pepper in small bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet and crumble.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons grease from skillet.
Add 1 onion and saut until transparent.
Stir in flour, sugar, 3/4 teaspoon salt, celery seed and oil/vinegar mixture. Simmer until slightly thickened.
Add potatoes, remaining diced onion, green pepper and parsley.
Toss together and heat through. Add crumbled bacon.
Serve hot.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Add celery, carrots and pineapple after Jell-O has cooked. Mix together Miracle Whip with cream, then add cottage cheese. Mix all together.
Nuts may be added if desired.
Chill and serve on crisp lettuce.

title: sauteed broccoli with walnuts
directions: Heat oil in medium skillet over low heat.
Add broccoli and garlic and saute over medium heat until broccoli is tender, about 10 minutes.
Add generous squeeze of lemon juice.
Stir in walnuts. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Heat through.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water.
Drain and mash.
Beat cream cheese.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients except paprika. Spoon mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from fridge 15 minutes before cooking.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: refreshing punch
directions: Just mix both ingredients in a punch bowl.
You may use more 7-Up if you want a thinner punch.

title: marguerite's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with whole pecans.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Line two loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch with aluminum foil.
Grease.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, then beat 3 minutes on high.
Spread mixture in pans.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove pans; cool.
Wrap in plastic wrap.

title: swiss ham ring around
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli.
In large bowl, combine parsley, onion, mustard, butter and lemon juice; blend well.
Add cheese, broccoli and ham; mix lightly.
Set aside.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: In a bowl, mix salmon, eggs and onions.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Shape into croquettes; fry until golden brown.

title: tony's favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pack firmly in a loaf pan. Pat top with flour.
Brush top with catsup if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil for the first 45 minutes. Uncover last 15 minutes.
Drain drippings and slice.
This is very moist.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown bacon and hamburger (if desired).
Drain well and place in casserole.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; cut into small pieces.
Drain 1/2 fat from frying pan.
Add onion, green pepper, pineapple and brown sugar.
Cook slowly until onion and pepper are tender.
Add pork and beans, Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Mix well and bake, uncovered, at 325° for an hour.

title: washington cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter; press onto bottom of a 9-inch springform pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and flour, mixing on electric mixer until well blended.
Blend in eggs, milk and vanilla; pour over crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature at 250°.
Continue baking 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool; remove rim.
Chill.
Top with pie filling before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook
pepper
and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in baking dish for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: jack-o-lantern cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 12-inch pizza pan with foil. Grease with cooking spray.
Beat corn oil spread, brown sugar, egg and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla until fluffy.
On wax paper combine oats, flour, soda, cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Spread batter into prepared pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Cool.

title: spanakopita (spinach pie)
directions: Cut filo sheets in half and place 10 pieces in an 11 x 7-inch pan, brushing pan and each sheet of filo with melted butter.
Wash spinach and remove stems.
Cut leaves in 1/2-inch lengths; mix with 1 tablespoon of salt and allow to stand 15 minutes.
Beat eggs.
Add parsley, onions and cheeses.
Squeeze liquid from spinach and fold into egg mixture.
Season with salt and pepper. Spread over filo sheets in pan and top with remaining 10 sheets of filo, brushing each sheet with butter.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain 1 jar of marinade into frypan.
Chop all artichokes and set aside.
Add onion and garlic to frypan and saute until onion is limp (5 minutes).
In bowl, beat eggs with a fork and add everything else.
Turn into a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares.

title: apple pan walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spread pie filling in bottom of pan. Combine sugar and flour. Sprinkle over pie filling. In mixing bowl, combine eggs, vanilla, oil and 1/2 cup nuts. Mix well. Pour over ingredients in pan. Stir only until blended. Smooth batter evenly in pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Pour topping over warm cake.

title: mushrooms and cream cheese appetizers
directions: Mix first five items and put on sliced bread that is buttered.
Broil until lightly browned.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool, then frost.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl. Pour into greased casserole dish.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bones; place in casserole dish.
Combine broth, chicken soup, poppy seed and sour cream; mix well.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Mix cracker crumbs with melted margarine; spread over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: basil carrots
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter or margarine; add the sliced carrots.
Sprinkle with salt and basil.
Cover skillet and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or just until carrots are tender.

title: original key lime pie
directions: Combine eggs and milk; mix well.
Add juice; blend well.
Turn into pie shell.
Top with meringue; bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: bread pudding(serves 6)
directions: Break bread apart into small pieces.
In a bowl, beat eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and sugar.
Add the bread to egg mixture.
Pour in enough milk to soak up the bread and mix well.
Add desired amount of nuts and raisins; stir.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted half way between center and edge comes out clean.

title: snowy mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash without milk.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic.
Beat at high speed until smooth and light.
Stir in chopped chives.
Spoon into lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with oleo.

title: ranchero dip
directions: Mix together and serve with chips, fresh vegetables, etc.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles in rapidly boiling salted water, about 10 minutes (1/2 teaspoon salt).
Drain and run under cold water.
Stir in all other ingredients (beaten lightly).
Bake in a large, well-greased baking dish for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Pound chicken breasts until 1/4-inch thick.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg mixture.
Combine bread crumbs, seasoned salt, pepper and oregano; dip chicken into crumbs.
Heat oil on medium-high.
Quickly brown chicken.
Remove to shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Pour excess oil from skillet.
Stir tomato sauce and basil into skillet; heat to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in butter.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover; bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on chicken.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Crumble ground beef into a large microwave-safe bowl.
Stir together soy sauce, sherry, flour, sugar, vinegar and gingerroot in 2-cup glass measure.
Add to ground beef; mix well.
Cover; chill 30 minutes.
Microwave marinated beef mixture, uncovered, on High 6 minutes or until beef is no longer pink, stirring twice during cooking.
Drain; keep meat warm.
Combine broccoli and onion in micro-safe casserole dish.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add to meat with hot pepper sauce; mix lightly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine oleo, sugar, corn syrup and water in a deep saucepan. Cook to 300°, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Put chips on top; spread until melted, then sprinkle with nuts.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: zucchini sausage pie
directions: Cook zucchini in water until tender.
Drain.
Cook sausage and drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except 2 tablespoons cheese.
Spoon into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: Clean spinach, drain, set aside.
Saute onion in 1 Tbsp. oleo.
Add spinach, no water.
Cover and cook on high 3-5 minutes. Spoon into blender, add 1 cup broth and process until smooth. Set aside.
Melt 3 Tbsp. butter, add flour and stir until smooth. Gradually add remaining broth; cook, stirring until slightly thickened.
Add spinach mixture and seasonings.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in half & half, simmer until heated thoroughly.
Top with croutons to serve.

title: bourbon glaze for ribs and chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Add oil, heat 2 minutes.
Add onion, cook until golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring frequently.
Cook until it forms a glaze, at low heat.
Excellent with ribs or chicken.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; spread on bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese, 10x sugar and the last 2 eggs together.
Spread evenly over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage treats
directions: Wrap sausage with bacon after rolling in biscuits or crescent rolls.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon lime ice cream
directions: Mix together and churn until ready.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix curry powder, garlic salt, sugar, horseradish, onion and vinegar.
Add sour cream and mayonnaise; blend well.
Cover and chill several hours.
Serve with small pieces of fresh vegetables.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable shortening or vegetable spray.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Add the other ingredients.
Mix together and serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Brown meat; drain.
Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook overnight or all day or put all ingredients in a pressure cooker and cook under pressure for 30 minutes.
Let go down naturally.

title: "microwave" peanut brittle(use large pyrex mixing bowl)
directions: In large Pyrex mixing bowl, put sugar and Karo; microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove and stir.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and butter and cook 2 minutes.
Take out and stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Immediately pour on greased cookie sheet.

title: raisin spice cake
directions: Boil on low heat raisins and 1 cup water until water disappears.
Then add balance of ingredients.
May add nuts, if desired.
Bake in bread pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
(This cake keeps very well.)

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine with sugar mixture; stir well.
Add chocolate bits.
Place in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Combine sugar, water, lemon slices and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Combine the juices and wine or cider.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for 10 minutes. Combine both mixtures and heat together.
Remove cinnamon sticks. Serve hot.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients. Add to first mixture. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Press down with potato masher dipped in sugar. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese and vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, combine water, cabbage, bacon, carrots, leeks and dry potatoes with sauce mix.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup and cornstarch.
Add frozen beans and simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes more until beans are tender.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup and cheese.
Cook broccoli to a rolling boil.
Drain. Add soup and cheese.
Cook rice.
Saute chopped onion in butter. Mix all ingredients together.
Top with Zesta cracker crumbs (1 cup).
Bake casserole 1 hour at 325°.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix any old way, adding Raisin Bran flakes last.
Fill muffin tins (or cupcake liners) 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp with linguine
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Set aside while starting boiling water for pasta.
Melt butter with olive oil in large skillet. Chop garlic and brown in skillet.
Add shrimp to skillet; cook just until pink.
Add wine and paprika; cook another minute or two.
Drain cooked linguine and put in large bowl.
Pour contents of skillet over linguine and toss.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender; drain. Put in 2-quart casserole.

title: blossoms
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg.
Combine dry ingredients. Mix all ingredients together except kisses.
Shape dough in small balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Immediately top with a kiss.
Makes about 36 cookies.

title: frozen fruit pizza (dessert)
directions: Mix ingredients and press into greased pizza pan.
Dough will be stiff.
Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Salt steak.
Cut steak into bite size cubes.
Flour cubes and brown in melted butter.
Add garlic, onion and mushrooms.
Brown slightly.
Add pepper.
Dissolve bouillon in water and add to mixture.
Simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Shortly before serving, blend in 1/2 cup sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cinnamon bread(yield: 3 loaves)
directions: Dissolve together yeast and lukewarm water.
Using a mixer set at medium speed, beat in next 5 ingredients.
Add 4 cups of flour gradually; mix will be runny.
Slowly add as much of the remaining flour as possible, until too stiff to beat.
Turn out onto a floured board and knead in rest of the flour.
Knead until smooth. (Should take about 10 minutes.)
Place dough in well-greased bowl and let stand until double in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: fresca verde
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, heat margarine and olive oil together on medium heat.
Lightly saut garlic, shallots and scallions for 2 minutes. Add peas, fresh chopped basil and sage and saut for 4 minutes. Add hot broth and simmer; when pasta is done, drain and mix into sauce.
Blend well and serve.
Serves 6.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine flour and meal.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour into greased iron skillet and bake on 250° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: fruktsoppa(fruit soup)
directions: Soak the dried fruits in the hot water at least 6 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat 1 hour.
Stir often to prevent scorching.
Serve hot or cold with cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: In saucepan or microwave, cook sliced squash and chopped onion in small amount of water until partially cooked.
Drain.
Combine soup, milk and sour cream.
Add carrots, onion and squash. Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread most of stuffing mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon squash mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
(If vegetable mixture seems dry, add more milk.
The stuffing mix will absorb excess moisture.)

title: fried deer meat
directions: Soak meat in milk and Italian dressing mixed together.
Let stay in this for 2 to 3 hours before cooking.

title: mom's barbecue sandwiches
directions: Add water and roast.
Cook in crock-pot according to cooking directions.
Remove roast when done and broth.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups broth for cooker.
Add onion, celery and green pepper to cooker and saute in a small amount of liquid.
Add remaining ingredients and reserved broth.
Shred roast with a fork, pulling into small pieces.
Add to crock-pot and cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours on simmer. Serve on buns.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with sour cream, mayo and garlic salt.
Using electric blender, chop shrimp cocktail.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: fruit cake(mom's)
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add the nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and mace. Add molasses and milk.
Add beaten egg yolks and mix well. Add the cherry juice, pineapple juice, flour, soda, vanilla, lemon extract and wine.
Mix well.
Mix together the currants, raisins, lemon peel, orange peel, citrus peel, pineapple, cherries, dates and walnuts and mix together with cake mixture. Add beaten egg whites last, folding them in.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Test for doneness.
Bake longer, if necessary. Toothpick should come out dry.

title: ambrosia sunshine cake
directions: Grease and flour (or spray) bottoms of 2 or 3 layer pans.
Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and vanilla in large mixing bowl at high speed until thick and lemon colored.
At low speed, add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Heat milk and butter in saucepan just to boiling.
Gradually add to batter.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan or Corning Ware first.
Then mix sugar, flour and milk in melted margarine.
Add peaches, stirring them in.
Let bake about 1 hour.

title: not meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Pour into greased baking dish and press down.
Set oven at 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: gobble-good turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy coconut candy *
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut, in double boiler. Cook, stirring, until smooth.
Stir in coconut.
Spread in buttered pan and cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to instructions on package.
Add margarine; stir until melted.
Add corn and soup.
Combine all ingredients; bake at 350°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle some cheese on top.

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onions in skillet until browned.
Place ground beef mixture in baking dish.
Add Tater Tots.
Combine soup and milk; pour over ground beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes with salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Add limas to mix.
Layer in casserole, beans and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven, uncovered.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until thick (can hardly stir).
Add peanut butter; let cool or make day before. Whip cream or Dream Whip; beat into the pudding mixture.
Put a layer of pudding in bowl, then a layer of bananas and repeat.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: mom almasy's brazil nut fruit cake
directions: Stuff each Brazil nut into each large date.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to fruits and nuts.
Add butter.
Beat eggs and add carefully.
Mix gently with hands.

title: wild rice casserole(minnesota delight!)
directions: Rinse both kinds of rice and cook them together with salt in 2 cups water.
Meanwhile, steam the vegetables briefly, 2 to 5 minutes. Toss rice and vegetables and turn them into a shallow baking dish. Top with cheese and almonds.
Cook under broiler until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Beat eggs.
Add melted oleo, sugar and salt.
Scald the milk and cool partly.
When yeast has dissolved in the warm water, add milk to it, then add to egg mixture.
Beat with beater.
Add 3 cups flour; beat again.
Now, I take a spoon and mix the rest of the flour in.
Let rise until double.
Roll out and spread with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut and make into rolls.
Let rise until double again.
Bake at 350° until done.
Grease top with butter, then frost.
Eat and get fat!

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter in electric skillet.
Stir in seasonings.
Blend well.
Add dry ingredients; mix.
Stir for 10 minutes over low heat, then cool.

title: french green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserving 1/2 the onions. Spoon into casserole dish and top with onions. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zora's chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken in large pot and cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Take chicken off bones.

title: "no peek" chicken(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Lightly grease casserole.
Mix first 6 ingredients and place chicken on top.
Sprinkle chicken with onion soup; seal with foil and bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Don't peek!
A "never fail" recipe.
Can be made ahead.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in greased casserole. Add soup and sour cream mixture. Sprinkle 1 roll of Ritz cracker crumbs on top. Melt 1 stick margarine. Pour on top of cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Double for 3-quart casserole.

title: old-fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Sift plain flour in large bowl.
Take a quart size boiler and pour about half full of cane syrup.
Add egg, cloves, allspice, ginger, cinnamon, soda, vanilla and salt.
Add all of this to syrup mixture.
Then work into flour with a big handful of shortening. Add mixture.
Roll out dough about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in squares. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes until brown.
Makes about 3 to 4 dozen.
(Use homemade syrup if you have it.)

title: low calorie fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese until smooth.
Add orange extract, pineapple juice and Equal. Mix well. Refrigerate until served.

title: peach jello
directions: Mix cream cheese and pineapple juice together.
Let Jell-O just start to gel.
Mix cream cheese, Jell-O and pineapple.
Pour into 7 x 9-inch glass pan.
Spread Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts over top.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: chocolate gravy with biscuits
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour together in pan.
Add milk, just enough to liquify.
Cook on medium heat.
When it starts to thicken, add butter.
If it's too thin, add some cornstarch.
If it's too thick, add more milk.
Pour over biscuits.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs if desired.
Bake 30-35 minutes in a 350° oven, uncovered.

title: snowball surprises
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with mixer until creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Stir in vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour and pecans, mixing well.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: next best thing to tom selleck
directions: Make cake following directions on box in 9 x 13-inch pan. Poke holes in cake with wooden spoon when it comes out of oven. Pour condensed milk and caramel over cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a large pot, cover chicken with water and boil until tender.
Remove chicken; debone and cut into small bite size pieces.
Reserve 1 cup of chicken stock the chicken made while cooking.
tags: cream of chicken soup or chicken noodle soup

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add rice and stir until rice is lightly browned.
Add water, tomato sauce and seasoning.
Stir well and cover.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: chicken saltimbocca ala romana
directions: Place each half of chicken breast on waxed paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Place a piece of Swiss cheese and Prosciutto in center of each half of chicken breast.
Roll up lengthwise and secure with toothpick. Combine flour, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic, salt and tarragon in a shallow dish.
Dip each chicken breast in egg, then coat with bread crumb mixture.
Brown chicken on all sides in 1/4 cup melted butter and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: peanut butter and jelly popcorn
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and jelly in a pan. Cook over low heat. Drizzle over popcorn.
Will make 2 quarts.

title: raisin bread
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Mix ingredients in a large bowl. Let rise 2 hours in warm place.
Separate dough into 2 equal halves.
Roll out dough.
Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon (1 cup sugar and 4 tablespoons cinnamon).
Put into 2 greased loaf pans.
Let rise one more hour.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Brush top of loaves with warm melted butter.

title: jalapeno bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 dish. Place peppers on bottom of dish. Sprinkle cheese on top. Pour eggs over cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine all fruits.
Add marshmallows.
Fold in cream and refrigerate.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Place shrimp in bowl.
Mix all ingredients and pour over shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate for about 1 hour (no longer).
Lift shrimp from marinade and thread 6 to 8 shrimp on skewer.
Place skewers on grill, turning as needed.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.

title: celebration salad
directions: Marinate asparagus in Italian dressing overnight, or at least 3 to 4 hours.
Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again. In bowl, blend mayonnaise, ketchup, horseradish, mustard and scallions; toss in macaroni, ham and celery.
To serve, arrange asparagus spears on platter; top with macaroni salad.
Garnish with watercress and cherry tomatoes.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix all ingredients well; put fish in batter, then fry in oil.

title: ranch artichoke spread
directions: Coarsely chop artichoke hearts and combine with dressing, sour cream and Parmesan cheese. Chill 30 minutes. Spread on crackers or sliced bread to serve.

title: parmesan zucchini
directions: Put whole zucchini into boiling water.
Boil for 4 minutes. Take out of water, slice longwise and place in baking dish.
Coat top of cut sides with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake until brown on top.

title: popcorn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Pour into greased 9-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Best served warm or toasted the next day.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together crushed pretzels with butter and sugar. Bake in a greased pan at 400° for 8 minutes.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together until creamy.
Add Cool Whip mix. Spread on first layer. Mix frozen strawberries with strawberry jello and boiling water. Let thicken a little.
Spread on second layer. Chill good before serving.

title: leek soup
directions: Dice and fry 4 slices of bacon until brown.
Leave bacon and grease in pan and add 2-inch diced onion and 2 diced leeks. Saute 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add 2 tablespoons flour and stir. Add 5 cups hot water with dissolved bouillon cube in each cup. Add 4 to 5 medium potatoes, diced.
Cook until potatoes are cooked.
Add sour cream with egg yolks beaten in with fork.
Add this mixture to soup, but first slowly add soup by the tablespoon to sour cream and yolks to prevent curdling.
Then add to soup. Garnish with parsley.

title: herbed roast pork loin
directions: Rub roast with olive oil.
Sprinkle with herbs, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place roast on a rack in a shallow pan.
Insert meat thermometer in thickest part of meat, not touching bone or fat.
Place in 350° oven and cook until meat thermometer registers 160° to 170°.
Let rest 15 minutes before slicing.
Use drippings to make a thin gravy if desired.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients together and spread on muffins. Freeze on cookie sheet until hard.
Cut into squares while still frozen.
Place in bags and keep frozen until ready to serve, then brown under broiler for a few minutes.

title: nana's fruit squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Mix butter or margarine with dry ingredients.
Add eggs last.
Mix until cookie dough texture.
Spread 3/4 of mixture on bottom of pan.

title: cheesecake
directions: Have first 4 ingredients at room temperature.
Place in bowl and beat with mixer.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Mix with mixer the next 3 ingredients.
Pour into pie pan and return to oven 10 minutes.

title: crisp and fluffy waffles
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry in a small bowl, set aside.
Beat the egg yolks well in a medium-size bowl and stir in milk.
Add dry ingredients and mix just enough to blend.
Add vegetable oil.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in a moderately hot waffle iron, 4 to 5 minutes, until crisp and brown or as iron manufacturer directs.
Serve hot with butter, syrup, honey or your favorite flavor of preserves, warmed.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix together and chill until jellied.

title: strawberry and rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Combine poppy seed,
buttermilk
and almond extract and set aside.
Cream butter; add
yolks and sugar and beat.
Sift flour, soda,
baking
powder
and
salt.
Add
flour
mixture alternately with buttermilk mix.
Beat egg whites and fold in. Pour 1/2 of batter into
greased and floured tube pan.
Sprinkle batter with 1/2 of mixture
of
1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Add remaining
batter
and
sprinkle
rest of sugar mixture.
Cut through
batter
with knife to give marble effect.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet-and-sour meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard. Combine meat, eggs, onion, green pepper, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Add 1 cup tomato sauce mixture.
Pack into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour 1/4 cup over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with meat loaf. Garnish with green pepper slices, if desired.

title: zucchini and pasta
directions: Puree tomatoes in blender for 10 seconds.
Place all ingredients in pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for approximately 1/2 hour.
Boil water for pasta.
Add sauce to cooked pasta.
Delicious with any shorter style pasta; ziti, rigatoni, trio Italiano, etc.

title: seashell salad
directions: Cook macaroni shells until tender. Rinse in cold water and drain well.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Make ahead.
Keeps well.

title: boston plum cake
directions: Mix well with a whisk the first 7 ingredients. Gradually add the flour until well blended. Pour into well-greased tube pan. Lightly drop pan to let air out of batter. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Chunk or slice potatoes thick (approximately 1-inch).
Slice celery thick.
Chop onion.
Cover all vegetables with water (not too much water, just enough to cover).
Boil vegetables until tender.
Add butter and spices during cooking.
Season to taste. Add cream of celery soup, milk, whipping cream and half and half; blend well.
Simmer for approximately 15 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Add ingredients together. Make into cakes.
Add more bread crumbs as you make your patty.
Eat and enjoy!

title: lemon chess buttermilk pie
directions: Melt
butter.
Add sugar, flour and cornmeal. Add eggs, one at a	time,
beating well after each addition.
Add lemon juice, lemon
peel
and
buttermilk.
Pour
into
unbaked 8 or 9-inch pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until a knife comes out clean and pie is golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and arrange on bottom of baking dish.
Precook chicken; debone it and lay it on top of the broccoli.
Pour the sauce over it (soup, mayonnaise and lemon).
Brown bread crumbs. Add cheese to casserole and then bread crumbs.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: creamed celery with almonds
directions: Cook celery for 5 minutes in boiling salted water.
Drain. Combine next 6 ingredients and add celery.
Pour in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: turtle cake
directions: Make cake mix as instructed on box, then add margarine and 1/2 can Eagle Brand milk and mix well.
Bake in 2 small sheet pans at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: omelet casserole
directions: The night before:
Put croutons in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cheese on top.
Pour 2 1/2 cups of milk, mixed with beaten eggs, over it.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: pumpkin loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Beat all ingredients at low speed for 30 seconds. Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Put 1 slice of each cheese and ham on each cutlet.
Spray pan with Pam.
Put each cutlet in pan and pour tomato sauce over each cutlet.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes.
You may use more sauce, if you like.

title: candy apples
directions: Combine water, sugar, vinegar, syrup and food coloring in large saucepan.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until candy reaches hard-ball stage.
Spoon over apples until coated.
Let stand on wax paper.

title: macaroni pizza
directions: Cook the macaroni dinner until done.
Add cheese from box and mix in eggs.
Mix well.
Brown the hamburger and drain.
Spread the macaroni in the bottom of 15-inch pizza pan.
Add the hamburger meat and spread the chopped onions on top of the meat. Top with the grated cheese and pour the sauce on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut like a pie.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Combine sweet milk, lemon juice, sugar and fruit; blend well. Add milk and water.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 1 gallon freezer.
Allow ice cream to ripen at least 1 hour.
Yield: 2 quarts.

title: fluffy spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir boiling water into corn meal; continue stirring until mixture is lukewarm.
Blend in 1 tablespoon margarine and the egg yolks.
Stir in buttermilk, salt, sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat egg whites just until soft peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells and drain.
Mix salsa, tomato sauce and water in large bowl.
Brown beef and drain.
Add 1 cup salsa mixture, 1/2 can of the onions and 8 ounces of the grated cheese to the beef. Stuff shells with this mixture.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar and blend.
Add eggs and cream.
Add all the rest; use a very large bowl.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes, depending on size.
I made walnut size balls, heaping up.
They didn't look done, but they are like chocolate chip cookies, they set up later.

title: easy cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Then spread whole graham crackers on top of foil.
Chop up nuts and put over graham crackers.
Cook margarine, butter and sugar together; let come to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes, then spread over nuts.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: honolulu chicken
directions: Mix preserves, barbecue sauce, onion and soy sauce.
Pour over chicken in glass baking dish (13 x 9-inches).
Add water chestnuts and green pepper.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice!

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add all the fruit and Cool Whip to mixture.
Pour into plastic freezer container and freeze. Remove 10 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and shape into a ball.
Sprinkle paprika over ball.

title: dilly ham balls
directions: In a bowl, combine ham, bread crumbs, onions, 1 tablespoon of dill, egg, mustard and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mix well; shape into balls.
In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of oil and 1 tablespoon margarine.
Brown ham balls; add remaining butter and oil as needed.
Remove balls to a serving dish.
Cover and keep warm.

title: pork chops
directions: Salt, pepper, and flour pork chops.
Fry them in a frying pan until brown on both sides.
Pour about 1/2 c. of grease (from frying pork chops) into a roasting pan.
Put sliced onions, potatoes, and pork chops in roasting pan.
Salt and pepper onions and potatoes.
Add 3/4 c. water to bottom of pot.
Put lid on and bake at 375 for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Make sure water does not cook out.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Mix together all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil one minute.
Remove from burner.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
These travel and keep well.

title: mildred's tomato aspic
directions: Spray or grease 9 x 9-inch dish or pan.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Dissolve gelatine in a little juice from tomatoes. Add to jello mixture.
Add balance of ingredients.
Stir well. Taste.
Congeal.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix in dish and pat down.

title: sour cream dip for fresh fruit
directions: Mix cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and salt with sugar.
Stir into sour cream.
Add extracts and mix well.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Spray 7 x 10 x 1 1/2 pan well. Mix pineapple, eggs, sugar, margarine and flour. Stir in bread cubes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix mayonnaise, onion, eggs and soup.
Pour over broccoli.
Melt margarine in pan and add roll of crushed crackers.
Heat until browned.
Top dish with crackers.
Cook in preheated oven (350°) for 35 minutes.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Crush crackers and place in mixing bowl. Add oysters and juice. Add melted butter and black pepper to taste. Add approximately 2 cans of chicken broth. Mixture should be consistency to pour easily (similar to cake batter). Add more broth or a little water if needed. Pour into greased 9-inch baking dish and bake at 425° approximately 25 minutes. Should be slightly brown on top. Let set for a few minutes before serving.

title: lavina fishel tesh's gingerbread
directions: Mix the lard with the treacle and water.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Beat the eggs to a froth and add them to the flour mixture with the treacle.
Beat all for a few minutes and turn into a deep baking dish, previously well-greased.
Cook in a slow oven for about an hour.

title: venetians
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat three 13 x 9 x 2-inch pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Line with waxed paper, allowing paper to come up the short ends.
Spray paper.
Break up almond paste in large bowl.
Add butter, sugar, egg yolks and almond extract. Beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy, 5 minutes.
Beat in flour and salt.
Beat egg whites with electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
Fold into almond mixture until well blended. Divide mixture into 3 equal portions.
Add green food coloring to one portion and red food coloring to another, leaving the last portion yellow.
Separately spread each colored portion into prepared pans.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until edges are golden brown.

title: tillamook cheddar cheese soup
directions: Cook onion in large saucepan over medium-high heat in butter. Blend in flour, mustard, pepper and nutmeg until smooth. Stir in milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickens and begins to boil. Remove from heat. Add cheese, stirring until melted and mixture is smooth and creamy. Serve hot with saltines.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Fold into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Roll in small balls and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook
chicken
breast
or
chicken until meat falls off bone. Cut up meat and save broth.
Mix sliced water chestnuts (including water),
celery, onion, almonds and prepared rice. Mix
soup, Miracle
Whip, lemon juice and chicken broth.
Add both
mixtures together with chicken and season with salt and pepper.
Mix in hard-boiled eggs and pour all the mixture into a
well
buttered casserole
and
cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake
for 20 to 25 minutes or until it bubbles.
May serve as a casserole or spoon into pastry shells.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in pan.
Add milk, butter, egg yolks and flavoring.
Cook until thick.
Add coconut and pour into cooked pie shell crust.
Add egg whites, stiffly beaten.

title: green tomato or cucumber crispies
directions: Soak tomatoes in 2 gallons water with 2 cups slaked lime for 24 hours.
Drain and soak 4 hours in fresh water, changing every hour.
Drain.
Make syrup of ingredients.
Bring syrup to boil. Pour over tomatoes and let stand overnight.
In morning, boil 1 hour.
Seal in jar.

title: stony gap slaw
directions: May substitute dill pickles or use 1/2 dill and 1/2 sweet.

title: bayou eggplant
directions: Peel eggplants.
Cut in half lengthwise and hollow out insides, leaving a 3/4-inch thick wall.
Combine milk with eggs to make an eggwash.
Dust eggplant shells with flour.
Dip in eggwash, roll in bread crumbs and deep-fry at 375° until golden brown.

title: surpriseburgers
directions: Wash lentils; add water and bring to boiling in large saucepan.
Lower heat; cover.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add onion and carrots.
Cook 15 minutes more or until lentils are very tender. Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Stir in bread crumbs, egg, garlic salt, oregano and salt.
Melt butter in large skillet. Drop lentil mixture by rounded one-half cupfuls into hot butter. Flatten mounds into patties with spatula.
Cook patties until firm and golden brown on both sides.
Top each patty with 2 cheese triangles; heat until melted.
Garnish with parsley sprigs and carrot curls, if you wish.

title: baked brussels sprouts
directions: Wash and discard any brown leaves from the Brussels sprouts. Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix Brussels sprouts with the onion, bread crumbs and cheese.
Add oil; stir together.
Bake until Brussels sprouts are fork-tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy cheesy chicken
directions: Rinse chicken, pat dry.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Place in slow cooker.
In a medium bowl, mix together soups.
Pour on top of chicken.
Cook on low for 6-8 hours.
Stir in sour cream before serving.
You can serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: copper kettle curry dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together one by one.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: snow cream
directions: Mix together first four ingredients, then pour over snow.
Be sure not to use the first inch of new snow.
It might be dirty.

title: pie crust
directions: Stir flour and salt together.
Blend in shortening until there are only tiny lumps.
Stir water in with fork.
Divide dough in half and put a piece of waxed paper on counter and roll out (the wax paper will help when putting dough in pie pan).
Roll out to fit in pie plate.
Add filling of choice or just bake crust at 350° for 8-12 minutes without filling.
Makes 2 9-inch pie crusts.

title: microwaved potatoes and carrots
directions: Cook carrots first in a large Corning Ware for about 6 minutes. Add potatoes, onions, margarine, parsley flakes, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup water for 8 minutes. Stir and turn dish half turn, if you do not have auto turn.
Cook an additional 6 or 8 minutes until tender. Cook, covered.

title: sourdough cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda, then mix in the salad oil, vanilla, vinegar and water. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick potato soup
directions: In saucepan, saute chopped onion.
Add soup, milk and water. Stir well and frequently.
Add dried beef (shredded); let simmer until flavors blend.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix together corn flakes and oleo.
Line bottom of baking dish with half the crumbs.
Place cabbage in baking dish over crumbs. Mix together the last 4 ingredients and pour on top of cabbage. Top with remaining corn flake crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: not so sweet pecan pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake until browned at 350°
makes 3 pies.

title: chocolate sunday pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and granulated sugar. Add egg, milk and
shortening.
Mix until smooth.
Blend in nuts. Spread into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine cocoa and brown sugar. Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over entire batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: wynona's jew chicken
directions: Clean and season chicken.
Place chicken in large pot with chopped celery, carrots and tomato soup.
Cook on stove 1 hour. Serve with rice and cornbread.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: "Get out of can, put in bowl, put pickles in it, and put mayo in it, mustard; stir it up.
Eat with spoon."

title: cake brownies
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Bring margarine, cocoa and water to boil in saucepan.
Pour liquid mixture from saucepan over the flour and sugar mixture in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour into cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Mix together into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
tags: Ore-Ida Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan (edges up slightly) and bake 20 minutes at 325°. Remove and allow to cool.

title: sausage show-off
directions: In skillet, brown sausage.
Drain off grease.
Melt butter in skillet with bell pepper, onion and corn.
Cook about 10 minutes. Add sausage; mix well.
In a large bowl, mix corn meal, egg and milk.
In another large skillet that has been preheated to about 450°, pour half of corn meal mixture, cheese and the other half of corn meal mixture.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, mustard and onion.
Mold into a loaf. Top with ketchup, rubbing the ketchup over the entire top of the loaf.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: lucy's sausage loaf
directions: Brown crumbled sausage and drain.
Shred cheese.
Let bread dough thaw and rise in a warm place, covered.
Punch dough down and roll out to a rectangle (14 x 8-inch).
Spread browned crumbled sausage and shredded cheese onto dough.
Sprinkle with oregano to taste.
Roll into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Let bread cool and set to firm slightly before slicing to serve.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Cut down center of the flounder to the bone, 1/4-inch from top to 1/4-inch of bottom.
Slice along center of flounder to within 1/4-inch of outside edge along top of bones.
Set aside.
Finely chop vegetables.
(Food processor works great).
Add chopped crawfish and crabmeat.
Add bread crumbs, eggs and spices.
Stuff flounder and round off top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until fish is done.
May also be frozen (before baking).

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly; cut each lengthwise into wedges or you may cube them.
Put butter and oil in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and place in hot oven to melt together.
Add potatoes and onions; toss to coat with butter.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika. Bake 1 hour or until tender, turning occasionally, at 325°.

title: cucumber and onion in sour cream
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and then add cucumbers and onions.
Cover and chill 24 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: spinach salad
directions: Place washed and dried spinach leaves on plate.
Top with 1 or 2 orange slices.
Top with thin sliced red onion rings and sliced egg.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add sour cream and cheese to butter and flour, blend until melted.
Mix with green beans and bake in a casserole dish for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hungry jack buttermilk peachy sausage bake(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan or baking dish.
In a large bowl, combine pancake mix, milk, oil and egg. Stir in prepared sausage and peaches.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 34 to 40 minutes, or until deep, golden brown.
Serve warm with Peach Maple Syrup.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hot cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Fill muffin tins about 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot hot caramel apples
directions: Peel about 3/4-inch off the top of each apple.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour juice over apples.
Fill the center of each apple with 2 tablespoons of sugar, 3 red hots, 1 tablespoon margarine and 2 caramels.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours or until the apples are tender.
Serve immediately with whipped cream if desired.
Serves 4.

title: spiced carrots
directions: Cook carrots with ginger.
Add cornstarch, orange juice, salt and sugar.
Cook until thickened.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Pour rice into glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish or larger.
Pour onion soup mix, then cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup.
Add water and stir.
Place 5 to 8 pieces of chicken on rice mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put a little oil in a skillet.
Saute chicken until it turns white.
Remove chicken and drain fat.
Saute onions and peppers and mushrooms (add more oil if needed).
Put chicken back.
Add uncooked rice, soup and tomato sauce.
Let boil.
Cover and simmer until rice is cooked.

title: brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Combine remaining milk (approximately 1/4 cup), cake mix and melted margarine.
Mix well.
Press half the cake mixture onto the bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and 1/4 cup walnuts over this layer.
Drizzle caramel mixture over this.
Top with teaspoonfuls of remaining cake mixture.
Press gently into caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining walnuts. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and then chill. Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add.
Refrigerate overnight or until firm.
Roll out, in hand, small balls and mash down with hand. Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 45 cookies.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9-inch round or 9 x 9-inch square pan at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Mix all other ingredients, except cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle cheese over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: lemon glazed crescent rolls
directions: Separate the rolls into triangles; brush with melted butter and sprinkle with the nuts.
Roll, starting with the large end. Bake according to directions for rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Glaze when cool.

title: christmas day brunch
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch casserole pan and line with cubed bread. Beat eggs with milk and mustard.
Layer bread with sausage, cheese and egg mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Combine hominy, margarine, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Heat until margarine is melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put into casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple open
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Peel and slice apples in water with 1 tablespoon lemon juice in it.
Drain apples.
Fold dry ingredients into apples.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Cut in 3/4 cup flour.
Sprinkle over apples in pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes.
If browns too much, reduce heat.

title: sherry's chicken biscuits
directions: You will need 1 large muffin pan.

title: goof balls
directions: Mix together until blended and refrigerate 3 hours.
Melt 1 tablespoon shortening and 12 ounces semi-sweet chocolate (dark or light may be used) in double boiler or microwave.
Shape above mixture into balls and dip into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: granola
directions: In large pan (roaster bottom) toast oats at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent scorching.
Add sesame seeds, sunflower seeds and wheat germ.
Mix and toast 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix in vegetable oil, honey and vanilla.
Toast 5 to 10 minutes more.
Remove from oven.
Add dried fruit.
Cool and store.

title: pear relish
directions: Chop all together in food chopper.
Cook until tender.
Put in jars and seal.

title: orange baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a shallow baking pan, breast side up, not

title: country-style fried cabbage
directions: Heat bacon fat in 10-inch skillet.
Add cabbage.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until light brown.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramels
directions: Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt butter; add sugar and salt and mix well.
Stir in syrup and mix well.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Continue stirring and cook to 245° or firm ball stage (about 12 to 15 minutes).
Pour into pan and cool thoroughly.
Cut with scissors and wrap in waxed paper squares.

title: grandma schrauder's grape-nuts pudding
directions: Beat together the dry ingredients and eggs, then add the hot milk.
Place pan in hot water and bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: shrimp
directions: Cook onion in melted butter.
Add tomatoes, bay leaf, salt, thyme, cayenne pepper and sugar.
Dilute mushroom soup with sherry.
Finally add shrimp and pimentos.
Cook 10 minutes.
Serve with boiled rice.

title: tennessee pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together; set aside.
In medium mixing bowl, cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients in four additions, alternately with water until just smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in nuts.
Turn into greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack to cool, right side up.
Store in tight container or wrap tightly and store in refrigerator.

title: baked beans
directions: Beans should be soupy when put into a glass baking dish. Feel free to thin with more ketchup, tomato sauce or water.
Cook slowly in a 325° to 350° oven for approximately 2 hours.
Stir from sides every 1/2 hour.

title: calico salad
directions: Drain liquid from beans.
Wash red kidney beans until clear. Add onion and green pepper.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Fold in peanut butter and sugar.
Roll in balls.
Flatten after placing on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Combine crem cheese, sugar, juice and rind, mixing until well blended.
Fold in whipped cream and coconut.
Spread mixture onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Freeze.
Combine fruit and marmalade; mix lightly.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fill shell with fruit.
Serve immediately.

title: mom's best requested rolls
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and potatoes to scalded milk.
When cooled to lukewarm, add yeast and mix thoroughly.
Add eggs and stir in enough flour to make dough very stiff.
Turn out on floured board and knead well. Place in a slightly larger bowl.
Cover with a cloth and let rise slightly.
Shape into balls and let rise to double.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, 1 1/2 cups brown sugar and vanilla; add egg. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in rhubarb and nuts. Pour in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix remaining brown sugar, cinnamon and ground or chopped nuts.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat
and onion until brown.
Salt to taste.
Heat soup, water, milk and chilies.
Combine meat and soup mixture. Line a large
pan with Doritos and pour meat-soup combination over it. Top
with grated cheese.
Brown it in oven from 325° to 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Freezes nicely.

title: randy's favorite candied sweet potatoes
directions: Wash 6 medium size potatoes.
Cook 15 minutes in boiling salted water.
Peel and cut into slices.
Put into a well-buttered baking dish.
Baste with a syrup made by boiling for 3 minutes 1 cup sugar, water and butter.
Bake in 350° oven until brown and candied.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg on top.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar and peanut butter with mixer. Blend mixture until it becomes crumbly.
Take 1/4 cup out and set it aside.
Add vanilla pudding to mixture and add milk.
Blend well.
Pour mixture into crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Cool Whip with mixture that was set aside in cup.

title: vegi dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: flan
directions: Combine the sweetened condensed milk, evaporated milk, and vanilla in a mixing bowl and mix well. Beat in the eggs. Sprinkle the sugar in the combination unit. Place the combination unit directly onto a burner preheated to medium. Cook until the sugar melts, holding the unit with a hot pad and turning the unit to coat the bottom and side evenly. Pour in the milk mixture. Place the combination unit on the 6-hole poacher rack over boiling water in the skillet. Cover the dome cover. Cook for 25 minutes. The cover should rattle slightly. Remove the combination unit from the skillet and let stand until cool. Place a large serving plate over the combination unit and invert onto the plate. Serve warmed or chilled. This recipe is an excellent choice for stack cooking. Cook the Flan on a 6-hole rack above any meal that is cooked in the Dutch-oven, increasing the cooking time to 50 minutes to allow for the lower heat: Yields: 8 servings.

title: southern baked chicken
directions: Boil chicken first.
Combine all ingredients, except chicken. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Bake chicken in a 325° oven for 1 hour, basting and turning at 15 to 20 minute intervals.
Cover; bake 30 minutes longer or until chicken is well done.
Serves 4.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Arrange broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and place over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple enchiladas
directions: Place 1 apple slice in each triangle of dough, rolling from larger end to smaller end. Place in a 9 x 13 baking dish. In a small saucepan, melt oleo, sugar and cinnamon. Pour over the enchiladas. Pour cola over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple glow salad
directions: Add juice to water to make 3/4 cup.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add measured liquid and lemon juice.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in pineapple and carrots.
Spoon into 3-cup mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours. Unmold.
Serve with salad greens and mayonnaise, if desired. Makes 2 1/2 cups or 5 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, syrup, salt, vanilla, sugar and butter.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400° and 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Filling will appear slightly less set in center.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; beat well, then add rest of ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 65 minutes.
Do not open oven for 55 minutes.
Cool in pan upright for 1 hour.

title: strawberry crush salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries, stirring until thawed.
Add crushed pineapple and pour into dish.
Place in refrigerator for 30 to 45 minutes or so until congealed slightly. Add bananas and allow to congeal completely.

title: pineapple surprise cake
directions: Preheat oven to bake 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large mixing bowl combine sugar, flour, pineapple, soda, eggs and pecans.
Stir by hand until mixture is smooth. Pour mixture into prepared cake pan; bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Allow cake to cool until it is barely warm to the touch, then ice with Cream Cheese Cake Frosting.

title: baked onion casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer onions in pan, covered with grated cheese.
Then crush potato chips.
Make three layers.
Mix the soup with milk and pour over onion and sprinkle with cayenne pepper.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs, sour cream and vanilla in a large bowl.
Mix 2 minutes at medium speed. Add flour, baking powder and soda.
Beat 1 minute at low speed. Spread half of the batter in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix together nuts, sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle half of the mixture over batter. Drop remaining batter in mounds on top and spread.
Sprinkle blueberries on top and sprinkle remaining cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Increase baking time if frozen berries are used.

title: bootlegger beans
directions: For every can of baked beans, use these ingredients.
Fry bacon halfway done.
Fry onion until soft in 1/2 bacon grease.
Place beans in baking pan.
Crumble bacon into pieces.
Add bacon and onion to beans.
Add brown sugar and molasses.
Mix and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Four cans serves 6 to 8.

title: oreo cheesecake
directions: Finely roll 30 cookies; coarsely chop 20 cookies.
In bowl, combine finely rolled cookie crumbs and margarine.
Press on bottom and 2 inches up side of 9-inch spring-form pan; set aside.
In bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Blend in eggs, sour cream and vanilla; fold in chopped cookies.
Spread mixture into prepared crust.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until set.
Cool on wire rack at room temperature.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Halve remaining cookies; remove side of pan.

title: caramel biscuit ring-a-round
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease a 12-cup fluted tube pan. In small saucepan combine sugar, nuts, margarine and water.
Heat until margarine melts.
Separate biscuits into 20 biscuits.
Place in large bowl.
Pour sugar mixture over biscuits.
Toss lightly to coat evenly.
Spoon biscuits into pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand for 3 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: good for you cookies
directions: Mix together well the brown sugar, oleo or Crisco, soda, salt, vanilla, eggs and flour. Stir in 1 cup flour, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Add the peanut butter, coconut, wheat germ or dry milk (add only one).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: party ham mold
directions: Reserve 5 slices of ham to line pan.
Cut remaining ham, slices into 1/2 inch pieces.
Soften gelatin in 1/3 cup water; dissolve in hot water.
Cool.
Reserve 1/4 cup cooled gelatin for ham slices.
Combine remaining gelatin with mayonnaise and mix well.
Combine diced ham, potatoes, celery, parsley, pimiento, onion, salt, pepper, and mayonnaise mixture.
Brush the inside of a 9 x 5 inch loaf pan with cooled gelatin.
Line bottom and sides of pan with 3 ham slices, arranging them so they will be slightly overlapping around the mold when it is removed from the pan.
Line each end of pan with a slice of ham, letting part of the slice extend over the slices to the bottom of the pan.
Brush ham slices, after lining pan, with remaining cooled gelatin.
Spoon potato salad mixture into pan.
Cover, refrigerate 8 to 12 hours. Unmold and serve on lettuce, if desired.

title: barbecue pork, chicken or beef
directions: Boil pork roast, beef roast or chicken until fully done.
Let cool and shred.
Mix all listed ingredients together.
Bring to a gentle boil for 20 minutes.
For milder sauce, adjust or delete Tabasco sauce.
Pour over shredded meat and mix well.
Will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.
Tastes better as reheated.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat until thick and fairly stiff.
Beat in one 12 ounce Cool Whip.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches, pineapple and oranges.
Mix juice with vanilla pudding.
Stir in fruit, then top with Cool Whip.

title: frito-bean salad
directions: Line bottom of a large bowl with lettuce. Add in layers the onion, green pepper, tomatoes and beans. Top with cheese, Fritos and Catalina dressing. Toss together just before serving.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to make a full cup of liquid.
Stir boiling water into Jell-O for 2 minutes, until completely dissolved.
Stir in pineapple juice mixture. Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours until slightly thickened.
Stir in Cool Whip with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes until mixture mounds.
Stir in pineapple, oranges and marshmallows. Spoon into 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours until firm. Unmold on plate and garnish with extra orange segments and lettuce.

title: cinnamon suckers
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup.
Stir until mixture dissolves then boil without stirring until hard crack stage.
Add cinnamon oil and food coloring and stir.
Then put on greased cookie sheet by tablespoonful to form sucker.
Use toothpicks for sticks.

title: kringles
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
Roll out in long string, a little heavier than a pencil and make into a figure "8" or a plain loop. Bake at 400° for 6 minutes or until rises on lower rack, then put on top rack and lightly brown.
Makes about 75.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine.
Blend at low speed until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Combine baking powder, baking soda and eggs to crumb mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour batter in prepared 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs and bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together then add eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add salt, soda and enough flour to make it stiff.
Spoon onto a greased cookie sheet by full teaspoons.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cabbage pot
directions: Layer beef, onions, cabbage and chopped or crushed tomatoes. Repeat as many layers as you like. Top with cheese. Simmer one hour.

title: turkey salad
directions: Toss all the ingredients together.
Serve cold.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, onion, egg, crackers and 1/3 of sauce.
Mix well. Spread on waxed paper.
Shape into flat rectangle.
On this, spread cheese and mushrooms.
Roll up and seal.
Cut in half. Makes 2.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; drain off fat.
Pour rest of sauce on top.
Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: angus sour cream cheese cake
directions: Grease 9-inch spring-form pan.
Put crumbs on bottom of pan and sides.
Save some for top.

title: fried chicken and milk gravy
directions: Soak cut, with skin removed, chicken in 2 cups milk for 1 hour. Place flour, salt, pepper and paprika in plastic bag.
Drain milk off chicken pieces.
Place few pieces in bag of flour and shake to coat well.
Have oil in skillet deep enough to cover chicken and moderate heat.
Place chicken and turn often until golden brown. Remove and drain on paper towel.
Pour up the oil and keep all the crumbs in skillet, pour in the can of evaporated milk, dash of pepper, dash of salt.
Let come to boil.
Serve over rice.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes.
Add rest of ingredients; cook for 45 minutes on a slow simmer after it comes to a boil.
Seal in jars.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour a 9x5x3 inch loaf pan. Combine the butter, sugar, and brown sugar in a large bowl. Beat until mixed. Add the eggs, vanilla extract and bananas and beat just until mixed. Gradually add the flour and mix just until blended. Stir in the walnuts.
Pour into the prepared pan and bake for about 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of loaf. Remove from pan immediately.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste and stewed tomatoes. Season with chili powder and garlic powder.
While this is simmering, cook macaroni or noodles until tender.
Drain and add to soup.
Serves 8.

title: individual quiches(makes 2 servings.)
directions: Prepare tart shells; refrigerated.
Place a small baking sheet in oven and preheat to 450°.
Cut bacon crosswise into 1/4 inch pieces.
Fry until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Beat egg and egg yolk in a medium bowl.
Blend in half and half.
Add salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Blend well.
Sprinkle bacon pieces evenly over bottom of unbaked shells.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over bacon. Pour half of egg mixture in each shell.
Place tart pans or preheated baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes until crusts begin to brown.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Bake 15 more minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: german coffee cake
directions: Spread dough in cake pan.
Save one cup of dough.
Spread any kind of pie filling over dough.
Drop the rest of the dough by teaspoon on the top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Eat hot with milk or ice cream.

title: yummies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour melted butter in another bowl and mix with 1 egg and cake mix.
Pat this mixture into bottom of baking dish.
Put a layer of chopped pecans over this.
Beat the other 3 eggs and add 4x sugar and softened cream cheese.
Pour on top of pecans.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let cool before cutting.

title: "artos" - bread for artoclasia
directions: Beat egg with milk; brush each round with egg mixture.
Bake at 350°.
As soon as the top appears golden, cover loosely with foil to prevent tops from becoming too dark.
The 9-inch rounds should bake 30 to 35 minutes; the 12-inch round should bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: good old banana bars
directions: Cream margarine or butter with sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix well, then add flour, baking soda and salt.
Fold in bananas and walnuts.
Dump into a greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Turn off oven; crack door and leave in oven overnight to cool. Next day, cut into bars and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: it's a different broccoli casserole
directions: Cook spinach and broccoli until thawed; drain.
Stir in cream of celery soup and tarragon.
Place mixture into baking dish.
Put sliced tomatoes on top.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese, then fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cover with foil for the first 35 minutes.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan:
