bread, sausage, cheese and mixture of remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine whipped topping and pudding mix in bowl.
Mix well. Fold in undrained pineapple, marshmallows and pecans. Pour in dish and chill until serving.

title: roberta's toffee bars
directions: *Original recipe calls for all granulated, also good with all brown sugar.

title: easy cheese sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine cheese and evaporated milk.
Stir mixture over low heat until cheese is completely melted.
Serve hot on baked potatoes, hot dogs or other sandwiches, etc.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix until oily ball.
Press in 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: ham and cheese souffle
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Spread half the bread cubes in the dish.
Add the ham and both cheeses.
Cover with remaining bread cubes.
Mix eggs, milk, onion salt and mustard. Pour evenly over bread cubes; refrigerate overnight.
Mix the butter with the corn flake crumbs; sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in butter.
Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Mix broccoli with celery, onion and mushrooms. Add soup.
Heat in a double boiler and add cheese.
Serve warm in a chafing dish.
Dip with Fritos or Melba rounds.
This can be made several days in advance and refrigerated.

title: chicken taco pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Retain broth.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Combine chicken, enchilada sauce, cream of chicken soup, onion, garlic salt and pepper.
Grease baking dish and line with Fritos.
Add chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover with Fritos.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup broth over Fritos.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Brown beef, salt, pepper and onions, stirring to break up meat until beef is done and onions are soft.
Pour off drippings. Alternate beef, potatoes and peas in 2-quart casserole.
Combine soup and milk; mix well.
Pour over top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large frying pan.
Saute onions over medium heat until clear.
Reserve some cracker crumbs for the top, but put 1/2 in the bottom of greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Remove onions from pan, drain.
Put into dish.
Layer onions, then soup, until all gone, then pour milk and egg mixture over top.
Put remaining crackers on top.
Top with cheese.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients (except chips) and beat.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and marbleize bars with a knife. Return to oven for 25 minutes.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Combine the soup, sour cream, chilies, green onion tops and the grated onion with most of the cheese.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups of the mixture without the chicken.
Now combine the chicken with rest of the mixture.
Fill the tortillas and roll up.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; seam side down.
Mix a small amount of milk with remaining sauce until consistency of thick gravy and pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika and more green onion tops if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6. Also a great treat the next day!!

title: fresh fruit
directions: Line an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with plastic wrap.
In saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over juice.
Let stand 2 minutes, then heat to simmer.
In blender, puree pears with lemon juice.
Add gelatin and blend.
Arrange raspberries in a row down each side of pan. Arrange orange slices down center, slightly overlapping.
Pour 1/3 of gelatin over fruit.
Now, arrange strawberries (half of them). Pour 1/3 of gelatin over.
Repeat with strawberries and gelatin. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Invert on plate and garnish with kiwi.

title: mediterranean chicken and "rice" salad
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C). In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, combine the soup, water, rice, okra, paprika and ground black pepper. Place the chicken on top of the rice mixture. Sprinkle with additional paprika and ground black pepper. Cover and bake in the preheated oven for 45 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through and the juices run clear. (For creamier rice, increase the water amount to 1 1/3 cups.)

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Add chili powder, paprika and oregano.
Stir to mix.
Add 1 cup hot water and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, tomato soup, 1 soup can water and the 2 cans of chili beans.
Simmer for 1 hour. Serve with chopped onion, grated cheese and/or sour cream.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip with Key lime juice.
Add condensed milk and blend.
Pour into pie crust and freeze.
Simple and very excellent!

title: guacamole dip
directions: Remove seed and mash avocado.
Ripe avocados are soft to the touch.
Mix all ingredients.
If you are not going to serve it right away, place the seed in the dip.
It will help keep it from turning brown.

title: how to make homemade sauerkraut(5 gallons)
directions: Shred 3
heads	of
cabbage at a time.	Mix in pan with 1/4 of salt
until it gets foamy.
Continue until the cabbage and salt are all gone.
Clean 5 gallon crock and plate (to fit in top
of crock)
by	scalding.
Fill crock with cabbage and salt mixture and
place plate and 1 quart jar of water on top for press.
Cover with
large
white cloth.	Let stand 4 to 6 weeks in dark and cool place (basement).
Then clean 1 inch or more off
top.
Can in quart jars.
Fill jars and process 1/2 hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on package and refrigerate to set.
Place one cake layer in bottom of 6-quart punch bowl.
Add, in layers, one-half of the ingredients in the following order:
prepared pudding, pie filling, fruit cocktail, pineapple, nuts, coconut and whipped topping.
Add the second layer of cake and continue in the same order, using the remainder of ingredients.
Garnish top with cherries, nuts or more coconut. Refrigerate.
Makes 35 servings.

title: cornish hens
directions: Clean and split hens.
Brush with melted butter.
Place the 4 pieces skin side down in a shallow baking dish.
Cover leg ends with aluminum foil.
Cover dish with wax paper.
Cook in microwave oven 8 minutes.
Remove foil.
Turn skin side up and transfer outer pieces to center.
Cook in microwave oven another 6 to 7 minutes.
Baste frequently.
Total cooking time: 15 minutes. Recipe yields 2 to 4 servings.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in medium bowl.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
(Can be prepared 4 hours ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.)
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour and baking powder that has been sifted together.
Add vanilla.
Add nuts.
If batter is too soft, leave in refrigerator for awhile to make firm.
Form into balls, then flatten.
Press dough lightly onto spread-out Rice Krispies.
Bake for about 15 minutes or until nice and brown about 1 inch apart.
Dough will spread.
Bake at 325° to 350°.

title: sweet-n-sour meatballs
directions: Trim the zucchini; halve them lengthwise.
Scoop out the seeds; cut the zucchini into French fry size pieces.
Transfer them to a bowl.
Set the oven at 400°.
Grease a rimmed baking sheet or jellyroll pan with 2 tablespoons of oil.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Put these ingredients in a clean 1 pound coffee can.
Put this coffee can in a 3 pound coffee can.
Put lids on both cans.
Layer alternately crushed ice and rock salt around the 1 pound can.
Turn the 3 pound can on its side and roll between two people for 10 minutes.
Open can and carefully open small can.
Scrape the insides of small can with a knife.
Repack ice and salt around can again.
Repeat rolling; check every 5 minutes.
If it's frozen enough, eat.

title: nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: peach-glazed pork tenderloin(save any leftovers for tasty sandwiches.)
directions: In a small mixing bowl stir together thyme, salt and pepper. Rub cooking oil into meat. Sprinkle herb mixture evenly onto meat. Rub in with fingers. Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 6 hours.

title: jello strawberry pie
directions: Put water, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat and add jello; stir until dissolved.
Put strawberries into crust and pour jello mixture over berries.
Chill 1 hour or longer.
Top with Dream Whip.

title: veal scallopini with tomatoes
directions: Cut veal into 1-inch squares; dredge with flour.
Brown in a mixture of butter and olive oil.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, milk, eggs, flour and baking powder.
Add fruit.
Bake 3 hours at 250°.

title: savory cornish hens
directions: Season birds with salt and pepper and put 1 bay leaf in each cavity.
Truss for roasting.
Arrange vegetables in roasting pan. Place birds, breast side up, on vegetables.
Combine butter with herbs and brush over birds.
Roast in 375° oven for 55 to 65 minutes or until tender, basting with pan juices.
Serves 4.

title: chili
directions: Saute ground chuck, garlic and onions in the olive oil.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for a couple of hours.
Serves 10.
Cooking time is 2 hours.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg yolks well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat egg whites last and fold in.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: french bread pizza
directions: Slice and cut bread in individual pieces.
Drizzle with olive oil (this prevents bread from soaking up pizza sauce).
Top with sauce and other ingredients.
Put on baking sheet and bake in 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until bubbly and bread is lightly browned.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and melted butter together.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Set aside for crust.

title: lemon pineapple pie
directions: Mix all together and form into crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.

title: cherry delight
directions: Butter cake pan.
Pour in pie filling.
Sprinkle with cake mix.
Pour melted oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (ovens may vary).

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse shrimp and combine all ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter or oleo and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, water and vanilla; mix well.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add flour, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoon.
Press with fork dipped in sugar to crisscross tops of cookies.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: pastina
directions: Bring the 6 cups water to a boil

in a saucepan. Add the salt, then the pasta. Stir slowly as the water returns to a boil so that the pasta doesn't clump at the bottom. Boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the pasta is tender. Without draining the pasta, add the butter and cheese and stir until both have melted. The mixture will be creamy, almost like a thick soup. Remove from heat.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat juice to boiling; add jello and sugar.
Add water, fruit and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Divide dough into two portions.
Form each portion into long square roll.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
(Overnight is best.) Slice and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not over brown.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and blend well.
Sift flour and dry ingredients.
Add this alternating with milk and sugar mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: Combine butter and sugar and heat slowly, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to hard crack stage (290°), stirring occasionally to prevent burning.
Add nuts and pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
When cold, melt the chocolate and spread over candy.
Sprinkle with more chopped almonds.
When firm, break into pieces.
This can be doubled.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries and marshmallows.
Add sugar.
Refrigerate. Next day, add apples, nuts and cream.
Mix together and serve.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a small baking dish, sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake until brown at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve with Triscuits.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and cake mix together.
Add water, oil and lemon juice.
Beat on low speed of mixer for 3 minutes.
Add whole eggs, one at a time mixing well after each egg.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for approximately 35 minutes at temperature indicated on cake mix box.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add flour; stir in milk and chicken broth and bring to boil.
Add the chicken soup, broccoli and carrots.
Salt and pepper to taste.
(It is easier to precook carrots in microwave so they will be tender earlier.)
Add 1 can of crabmeat, if desired.

title: ben burnside's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add egg yolks and beat well. Add flour, milk and soda; mix well. Add vanilla and almond flavoring; mix. Beat in egg whites. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: instant banana pudding
directions: Mix instant vanilla pudding per package directions.
Add to pudding, sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and sauce; continue until gone.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: no mix six layer cake
directions: Melt oleo and put aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, ungreased, spread pie filling, then spread pineapple and sprinkle dry cake mix.
Pour oleo over cake mix.
Sprinkle on coconut and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain string beans.
Then mix string beans and mushroom soup good, until blended well.
Spread on cheese, then French fried onions.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: fresh strawberry  pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, cornstarch and salt; cook until clear. Remove from heat. Add red food coloring.
Add gelatin; stir well. Let cool.
Put strawberries into baked pie shell.
Pour sauce over strawberries.
Chill.
Top with whipped
cream before serving.

title: coffee walnut candy
directions: Combine brown sugar, white sugar, sour cream and instant coffee in saucepan.
Cook and stir to soft ball stage (236°). Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Add walnuts and stir gently until all walnuts are coated.
Arrange single layer on buttered cookie sheet.
Separate nuts with fork or let mixture dry then break into pieces.
Makes 4 cups.

title: cherry bourbon jelly
directions: Drain cherries, reserving fruit and 1 1/2 cups of juice. Combine the juice with pectin; bring to a boil.
Add sugar; return to a rolling boil and boil for one minute, stirring constantly. Add bourbon and cherries.
Pour into hot jars and cover at once with hot paraffin.
Makes 4 to 5 cups.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Baste chicken with 1/2 of the mixture.
Broil 20 minutes.
Turn and baste with remaining sauce.
Broil 20 minutes.

title: easy baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on pork chops.
Place pork chops in large flat baking dish or pan and spread with about 1/2 of tomato paste.
Top each pork chop with onion slice and bell pepper rings.
Mix remaining tomato paste with water and sprinkle over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: caper salad
directions: Chop green olives into small pieces; add drained capers and bread crumbs.
Mix together.

title: picante beans and rice
directions: Cook rice.
Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix beans, rice, hamburger and 1 cup cheese; pour into casserole dish.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional 2 tablespoons cheese; cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the above.
Form into loaf or ball.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or
until done.

title: mrs. gay sloan's old fashion custard
directions: Heat milk until a skin comes on the top.
Add sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add eggs and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake until firm or until a silver knife comes out clean when inverted in center of pie.

title: pierogies ala pam(low-fat)
directions: Saute onions in pan sprayed with Pam until tender.
Add tomatoes and saute an additional minute.
Add broth, milk and cheese; stir until thickened.
Place pierogies in casserole dish. Top with onion mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Boil rice with soup and water in pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; shape into oval patties.
Brown on both sides in butter.
Combine soup and water and pour over and around meat.
Cook slowly in covered skillet for 25 minutes.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Cut sausage lengthwise into 4 pieces.
Cut each piece into 1/2-inch slices.
Brown in large Dutch oven.
Drain; reserve drippings.
Brown chicken in pan drippings.
Drain.
Combine oil and flour in Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until roux is the color of chocolate (about 30 minutes).
Add minced onion and next 3 ingredients; cook until tender.
Add water; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Add chicken, Creole seasoning and hot sauce.
Cook, uncovered, 1 hour.
Remove chicken; set aside to cool.
Add green onions and parsley to gumbo.
Bone chicken and coarsely chop.
Add chicken and sausage to gumbo.
Heat.
Ladle gumbo over rice into bowls.
Yield: about 3 quarts.

title: stuffed green pepper soup
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Drain.
Brown ground beef.
Drain. Heat all ingredients together to a boil and reduce heat to simmer for about 1 hour.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a blender set on high speed for exactly 1 minute.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat
eggs.
Add
oil, water and pumpkin and beat well. Sift together and add dry ingredients to mixture.
Pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch or 6 miniature loaf
pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for large pans and 30 minutes for miniature.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk together.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef.
In baking dish, cook Tater Tots for 10 minutes at 425°.
Then add in layers over Tater Tots:
ground beef, broccoli, onion rings, cheese and soup mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.
Add more cheese and onion rings and bake 15 minutes more.

title: ham and eggs bravo
directions: Blend flour, salt and pepper into mayonnaise; gradually add milk.
Heat, uncovered, on Roast for 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Add cheese and heat, uncovered, on Roast for approximately 1 1/2 minutes, or until cheese has melted. Add onion, pimiento, ham and eggs.
Heat, uncovered, on Roast for 3 to 5 minutes or until heated to 140°.
Serve on muffins.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, soup, sour cream and onions.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Put half the stuffing in casserole dish.
Pour in squash mixture and cover with other half of crumb mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nacho dip
directions: Put Velveeta into a large crock-pot and add about 1 cup water to thin.
Brown and crumble sausage and add to melted Velveeta. Dice, slice or peel and smash peppers (just use 2 to 3 tablespoons of the juice if you prefer to not bite into the peppers).
Keep the crock-pot turned on while heating the dip or it will cool off too much.
If necessary, milk can be added to thin the dip if the crock-pot has been on a long time.

title: golden chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat butter, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate bits.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: favorite applesauce pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together thoroughly and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 275° and bake for one hour.

title: fricasseed chicken with acacia honey
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
Heat oil and butter in a heavy skillet large enough to hold chicken pieces in one layer.
Add chicken, skin side down, and cook until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Do not cover.
Drain off fat and add shallots and onions.
Stir and cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until onions are light brown.
Add bay leaves and thyme. Stir and add wine, cream, chicken broth, lemon juice and honey. Bring to a boil; stir and scrape bottom of skillet.

title: quick cheeseburger bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook beef and onion in skillet until browned; drain.
Stir in soup, veggies and milk.
Stir Bisquick and water in baking dish until moistened; spread evenly.
Spread beef mixture over batter. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes or until browned.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Combine milk and Bran.
Stir until soft.
Add egg and cooking oil.
Beat. Add flour mixture, stirring only to combine the ingredients.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: el patio special
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Layer corn tortillas, beans, meat, lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Repeat.

title: bobbie's hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all only until combined.
Cook in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: catfish lemon basil bake(low fat)
directions: Sprinkle catfish fillets on each side with lemon pepper seasoning and dried basil.
Place on a baking sheet that has been coated with cooking spray.
Lightly spray the top of each fillet with the butter flavored cooking spray.
Bake at 375 degrees for about 25 minutes or until tender.

title: bread(french)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2/3 cup warm water; allow to foam.
In a large bowl, combine butter, salt, sugar and hot water.
When
this mixture is lukewarm, combine with yeast.
Add flour a little at a time.
After 4 cups, beat dough vigorously for 10 minutes, then add rest of flour.
Knead until elastic.
Form into ball and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise 1 hour.
Butter baking sheet and sprinkle corn meal over the butter.
Divide dough into 3 loaves.
Cover with towel and let rise until doubled.
Brush with cold water.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for
1 hour.
Every 15 minutes, brush top with cold water for hard crust; keeping a pan of water in oven will help make it crusty also.

title: orange slice
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Dissolve soda in milk.
Add to mixture.
Place flour in bowl.
Add dates, candy and nuts.
Stir to coat pieces.
Add cream mixture and coconut.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: blaylock frozen salad
directions: Cook oleo, eggs and sugar until thick.
Cool.
Mix fruit with cooked
and
cooled
mixture.
Add Cool Whip; pour into 1 oblong container
or 3 ice trays and freeze.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: onion dip
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and chill. Stir before serving. Serve with fresh vegetables or potato chips. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: marie underwood's pie filling cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add gently to batter, mixing well; add vanilla.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Spread half of batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle with half of sugar/cinnamon.
Spread on pie filling.
Repeat with batter; top with cinnamon/sugar.
Bake at 350° for
about 45 minutes.

title: breaded brussels sprouts
directions: Dip Brussels sprouts into egg; roll in crumbs and fry in hot deep fat (380°) until browned.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and crunchy sauerkraut salad
directions: In bowl, combine sauerkraut, celery, green pepper and onion.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil, stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over kraut mixture, toss, cover and chill 3 to 24 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: clairmont diner coleslaw
directions: Mix and marinate for 3 days.
Stir often.

title: homemade chili
directions: Fry hamburger with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Drain hamburger and add the remaining ingredients and slowly cook for about an hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water until dissolved.
When cooled add cranberry sauce and sour cream.
Mix well and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and chill.
Serves 15.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half crosswise.
Sprinkle cheese, parsley and onion over cut surfaces.
Place tomatoes in small baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Pour melted butter in baking dish.
Mix together flour, milk and 3/4 cup sugar and pour into melted butter.
Mix water and fruit.
If fresh fruit is used, add 1 cup sugar.
If canned fruit is used, add only 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir into butter and flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Thaw frozen strawberries. Mix all fruits together.
Pour Jell-O over mixture.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in a flat bottom dish.
After it has congealed, spread sour cream over top, then pour rest of mixture over sour cream. Return to refrigerator to finish congealing.

title: spinach balls
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Add onion and garlic; saute until golden (10 to 15 minutes).
Add spinach, salt and pepper.
Cover and turn heat to its lowest point; steam for 5 minutes.
Remove; stir in bread crumbs, cheese and eggs.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Oil a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish (baking) and cover bottom with tomato sauce.
Roll spinach mixture into 2-inch balls; place in tomato sauce.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes and serve.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Cover bottoms of 2 graham cracker pie crusts with sliced bananas.
Cream (8 ounces) of cream cheese with 2 tablespoons of lemon juice.
Slowly add 1 1/2 cups of powdered sugar until smooth.
Using container of Cool Whip, cover bananas in pie shells.
Chill for 1 hour and add 2 cans blueberry pie filling. Spread on top of pie and chill.
Recipe makes 2 pies.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Pile lightly into greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cover with chips.
Bake until chips brown.
Make sure to watch close; chips brown fast.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Dissolve soda in a little warm water.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, bananas and salt.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into two 8-inch pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Mix corn, olives and cheese together.
Add tamales, sliced to bite-size.
Mix lightly.
Bake in 3-quart casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix together. Spoon over meat of your choice.
Cover kettle. Cook for 15 minutes.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Lightly beat egg, then mix in oil, juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Squeeze in garlic.
Lightly blend together and refrigerate in closed container.

title: german macaroni salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and add mayonnaise to taste. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water with bay leaf.
Remove from bones and cut into small pieces.
Cook spaghetti in the water that you cooked the chicken.
Make soup according to package directions for time and amount.
Melt butter.
Saute celery and onion.
Add flour; stir constantly.
Add soup, chicken, spaghetti and cheese. Put into a greased casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: italian chicken
directions: Put chicken in a dish and pour Italian dressing over it.
Cook at 400° for 20 minutes.
Then place rice and veggies under and around chicken and pour over broth and seasoning (mixed).
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350° or until rice is done and broth is soaked up.
(For brown rice, reduce to 300° and cook longer.)

title: reese peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and add sugars.
Add eggs and peanut butter, mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, mix.
Shape into small balls.
Place in miniature muffin tins.
Poke hole in center with thumb.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Unwrap miniature Reese's. Remove cookie from oven and push Reese's cup into each cookie.
Let cool in tin.

title: tea syrup
directions: Bring water to a boil; remove from heat.
Add tea leaves.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Remove tea leaves.
Add sugar and cool.
Put in freezer box and freeze.
To serve, use 1 part syrup to 3 parts water.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar, water and lemon juice in a large saucepan; cook until cranberries pop.
Stir in jello and marshmallows until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Cool, then stir in nuts, celery and apple.
Pour into large mold and chill until firm.

title: english plum pudding
directions: Chop the suet finely; cut the peel into small pieces.
Put suet, currants, raisins and peel in large bowl.
Add lemon rind, sugar, spices, flour and bread crumbs.
Moisten with the well-beaten eggs and grape juice.

title: mom's magical muffins
directions: Combine the cereal with the sugars, flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl.
Whisk the eggs with the buttermilk, oil, and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Add the wet ingredients, all at once, to the dry mixture and stir by hand until just moistened.
Fold in the raisins, dried pineapple and the toasted almonds.
Cover tightly and store in the refrigerator.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Shred a quartered small cabbage as for coarse cole slaw.
Cook quickly in covered pan with a little water to keep from burning. Cook just until tender-crisp, 5 to 15 minutes for green or white cabbage.
Drain thoroughly; season with salt and pepper.
Put butter and celery in saucepan.
Cook slowly 5 minutes.
Stir in flour; blend.
Stir in 1 cup milk slowly.
Cook until thick.
Stir constantly for about 5 minutes.
Season to taste.
Add cabbage. Spoon into baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Cover with crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake at 325° to 350° until well heated and browned on top. Serves 4 or 5.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, butter, garlic, salt and seasoned salt.
Add crabmeat.
Cut each muffin in half; place on cookie sheet.
Spread crabmeat mixture on each half muffin; cut into quarters.
Place cookie sheet in freezer.
Remove to container; keep frozen until ready to use.
Place appetizers back on sheet. Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes, or until done.

title: oriental crab meatballs
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except egg, cornstarch and oil.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in cornstarch, then in beaten egg.
Drop into hot oil and fry until golden. Drain and keep warm until served.
Good with cocktail sauce or a white horseradish sauce.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add sour cream and margarine.
Beat well.
Mix in sour cream.
Add milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until lightly brown.

title: hershey pie
directions: Bake and
prepare
pie	crust according to crust directions. Slowly
melt
large Hershey bars (about 4).
Pour into prepared crust.
Refrigerate until very firm.

title: cheese straws
directions: Nucoa needs to be at room temperature.
Mix Nucoa and cheese together.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add to cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Very good.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and a little sherry.
Place some beef on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan, then chicken, sauce and mushrooms.
Keep alternating with sauce, mushrooms and almonds on top.
Do not add salt.
Cover pan with foil tightly and bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil and add stuffing.
Recover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours more.
If you do it the night before, just do the first baking.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hearty and spicy cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain off fat.
Set aside.
Melt cheese and stir in tomatoes and milk.
Add meat.
Serve warm.

title: tasty vegies
directions: Microwave bags 2 or 3 minutes per bag on High or just defrost. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.
Cut cheese into cubes and add to top.
Crush crackers and add to the top.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange dream
directions: Tear angel food cake into small pieces and lay in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with oranges, saving a few for garnish. Dissolve jello in water.
Add sherbet and stir until dissolved. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped cream and pour over oranges and cake.
Garnish with remaining oranges and chill overnight.

title: savory spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Stir until crumbled and no longer pink. Drain mixture. Return to Dutch oven. Stir in marinara sauce, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes. Stir in diced tomatoes, tomato sauce, dried Italian seasoning, dried basil and mushrooms. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. This makes a large pot of sauce. It freezes well.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Place roast in slow cooker (or pan in oven).
Cover roast in oven and bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut together.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over nut and coconut mixture.
Now mix melted oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy.
Spoon on top of bake batter (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Check to see if done after 45 minutes.
If not, cook 5 more minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Add first four ingredients and bring to a boil for 5 minutes. Remove from burner and add baking soda (this will cause mixture to foam).
Pour over popcorn.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: corn souffle
directions: Melt margarine.
Add all other ingredients and mix until moistened.
Pour into lightly buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers using fine blade. Mix with sugar and vinegar and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add pectin and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Pour in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Jelly may be strained before adding pectin to make it clear.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with one stick of melted margarine. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other stick of margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Beat with electric mixer for 15 minutes. Pour over crust.
Slice bananas lengthwise and lay side by side on sugar mixture.
(Dip bananas in lemon juice to keep from turning dark.)
Drain pineapple and spoon over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Garnish with nuts and cherries, if desired.

title: four stack dessert
directions: Mix and pour first 4 ingredients into 11 x 13-inch pan. Spread evenly on bottom of pan with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese, then fold in Cool Whip and spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk and spread on cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip and grated chocolate. Refrigerate.

title: beef rice dinner
directions: Prepare rice oriental dinner as directed on package, except omit water.
Add enough water to beef broth to measure 3 1/3 cups liquid.
Five minutes before end of cooking, stir in Chinese vegetables and green pepper.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: peach pickles
directions: Add peaches and syrup.
Process in boiling water bath 25 minutes.

title: brennan's bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the sugar and butter. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add the whipping cream slowly.
Add the cinnamon, vanilla and raisins. Spray an 8 x 14 x 2-inch Pyrex dish with Pam.
Place bread cubes in Pyrex dish.
Arrange bread cubes in one layer, tightly packed. Pour mixture over bread cubes and allow to stand 10 minutes.
Press until the bread cubes are covered with the mixture.
(If mixture does not cover all of the bread cubes, you may add as much as 1 cup of milk to increase mixture).
Cover Pyrex dish with foil.
Set Pyrex dish in a larger pan.
Fill larger pan with water to 1/2-inch from top.
Place in oven.
Set timer and bake for 35 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes or until browned but still soft.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Combine everything but the relish and cooked pork.
Slowly simmer for 2 to 3 hours until thickened.
Add pork.
Just before serving, add the relish.

title: fat man's pie
directions: Mix crust ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 300 degrees for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix ingredients (in a greased mixing bowl), let rise overnight (will double in size).
Knead ingredients, divide and put into 3 greased bread pans.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When you take a cup of starter out of your pint jar, replace it with:
3/4 cup sugar or honey, 1 cup warm water and 3 tablespoons instant potatoes.

title: mock champagne cocktail
directions: Just before serving, mix carbonated beverage and apple juice. Serve in stemmed glasses with lemon slice.

title: marinated cauliflower
directions: Wash cauliflower and break into flowerets.
Put all ingredients in large pot and bring to a boil.
If cauliflower is too large, add water to cover.
Boil about 10 minutes and allow to cool.
Turn into bowl and chill at least 24 hours.
Drain for several minutes. Serve as an appetizer or as a salad.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients. Do not beat and leave batter lumpy. Pour individual-size pancakes onto griddle at 350° to 400°. Flip when side becomes saturated with bubbles, then cook until golden brown on bottom. Yield: about 12 to 16 medium cakes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve over lettuce salad.

title: hobo bread
directions: Cook the water and raisins 10 minutes and cool.
Cream together the butter or margarine, sugar and eggs.
Mix with the cooked raisins.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add to raisin mixture.
Pour in well-greased coffee tins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes or so and remove from coffee tins onto cooling rack.

title: royal bibingka
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 round 9-inch cake pans. Pour boiling water
over
banana leaves; line pans with wilted leaves. In large
bowl, beat eggs until light.
Gradually add the
3/4 cup sugar,
beating
well.
Sift
flour
and
baking powder; add alternately
with
coconut milk to cream mixture. Pour into prepared
pans.
Bake for 20 minutes, then broil for 7 to 10 minutes,
or until lightly browned.
Brush each layer with butter; sprinkle
with
teaspoon
sugar and the grated coconut.	Makes 16 servings.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in jar and mix well.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix dressing mix, cream cheese and mayo or Miracle Whip. Spread mixture on bread. Place sliced cucumbers on top of mixture. Sprinkle with dill weed. Place bread on top.

title: mock baby ruth bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; pour melted butter over mixture and stir.
Add 1/4 cup peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips over hot water.
Add peanut butter and nuts.
Spread on top of bars.
Cool and cut.

title: shrimp floridian en papillote
directions: Mash cheese and cream cheese; add parsley, chives, garlic and wine to make a sauce.
Pour sauce over raw shrimp.
Bake in a covered baking dish for 30 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4.

title: pasta salad
directions: Clean vegetables and pour boiling water over them, then rinse in cold water.
Marinate in Italian dressing overnight.
Cook rotini noodles and add pasta to vegetables.
Then sprinkle with 1 or 2 packages dried Italian mix.
Add ham or chicken or shrimp. Refrigerate.

title: cheese straws from alabama
directions: Grate cheese and mix with flour, salt, pepper and baking powder.
Let butter soften and work into the mixture with your fingers.
Shoot through a pastry gun or make into small balls and press them very flat with a fork or roll out to about 1/4-inch and cut with a small biscuit cutter.
Optional:
Top with a pecan. Bake at 300° to 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes, but be sure they are baked through.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: tangy microwave cauliflower
directions: Wash cauliflower, removing all leaves.
Shake but do not blot dry.
Place in large casserole (1 1/2 to 2-quart), covering with lid or plastic wrap.
No additional water is necessary, as cauliflower will use moisture remaining on head from washing. Microwave for 9 minutes on High.
While cauliflower is heating, mix salad dressing (mayonnaise may be used) with mustard, dried onion, salt and pepper.
Spoon dressing mixture over cooked cauliflower; sprinkle top with cheese and paprika.
Microwave for 1 1/2 or 2 minutes on Medium-high, or until cheese is melted. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine cocoa, water and soda.
Sift into bowl flour, sugar and salt.
Add cocoa mixture, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and butter.
Work into fine crumbs. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of crumbs for topping.
Add rest of ingredients; beat well until mixture is very thin.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan roll
directions: Melt morsels over hot water in double boiler.
Add milk and mix.
Stir in vanilla.
Shape into 2 rolls.
Roll each in pecans. Wrap in waxed paper, then in foil.
Chill for 3 hours.
Slice.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together the butter, sugars and eggs. Beat in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: spaghetti special
directions: Combine spaghetti, eggs, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes (1/4 cup). In 2 (11 x 9-inch) baking dishes (greased), layer 1/2 of spaghetti and Mozzarella cheese; repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with following sauce.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Saute onion, carrot and green pepper in butter until onion is tender, not brown.
Add beef, cooking only until color's lost. Stir in tomato juice, potatoes and seasoning.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Combine flour with a little milk to make a paste.
Add to soup, stirring until smooth.
Add remaining milk and heat (don't boil!), stirring frequently.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, cool and remove from bones.
Save broth.
Saute pepper, onion and celery in the butter.
Cook noodles in chicken broth until done; drain.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Then make 1 large or 2 medium size casseroles.
After mixing it may be frozen and kept for later use.

title: crunchy nutty delight
directions: Line bottom of 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan with whole graham crackers.
Sprinkle one-half of the chopped nuts over crackers. Bring margarine, butter and sugar to a boil in a saucepan.
Boil 90 seconds.
Pour sugar mixture over crackers and top with remaining nuts.

title: bright and early morning chow
directions: In a cake pan, melt a stick of butter.
Layer your peppers and then pour egg mixture over the peppers and top with the Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: coconut pie(makes own crust)
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given and mix well.
Pour into a greased glass pie pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve with strawberries, bananas, pineapple, grapes, oranges, apples and kiwi.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine cocoa, butter, water and sugar in a saucepan over medium heat.
Stir frequently until mixture comes to a boil. While mixture is cooking, put dry ingredients in a large bowl. When cocoa mix boils, add it to the dry ingredients, mixing as you add.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Combine thoroughly, but do not beat.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 1/8-inch) and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Begin to prepare the frosting 5 minutes before the cake is done. Let cake stand 5 minutes and frost immediately.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: In a small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat together first three ingredients until soft peaks form. Gradually beat in sugar until smooth and glossy. Gradually beat in corn syrup and vanilla until stiff peaks form.
If desired, beat in food coloring.
Makes enough frosting for 9-inch layer cake.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish. Pour soup that has been diluted over top.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except biscuits and cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Add cheese on top.
Cook biscuits separately.
After 30 minutes of cooking casserole, top with browned biscuits.
Serve.

title: stromboli
directions: Unroll pizza crust; spread pizza sauce over crust. Sprinkle on Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and oregano. Fill pizza crust with meats/vegetables. Roll up like jellyroll. Stick toothpicks in on top and sides to hold together while baking. Be sure both ends are shut tight. Brush with 1 beaten egg. Sprinkle top with Parmesan and oregano. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in oatmeal and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips.
Bake for 25 minutes or until light brown.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and salt and pepper to taste. Cut up potatoes and carrots.
Put in another pan; add corn, green beans and tomato sauce.
Drain meat and add to the other ingredients.
Let simmer for about 2 hours or until potatoes and carrots are done.
Serve with corn bread.

title: curried tuna
directions: Cook rice as directed; mix remaining ingredients and heat until bubbly.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.
I like to mix with rice and lightly bake in oven.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix and cook until hot.
Put in canning jars; seal tightly.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with hunks of Italian bread or crackers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well with mixer.
Pour into loaf pans (3).
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: microwave fudge
directions: With whisk, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and oleo.
Do not stir.
Cook on High 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Put into fridge until set.
Freezes well.

title: bon-bons
directions: Mix together Eagle brand milk, oleo, powdered sugar, coconut, nuts, and vanilla.
Let set overnight.
Dip small balls of mixture into melted chocolate chips and paraffin.
Place on wax paper.

title: peanut ice cream pie
directions: Press ice cream into crust.
In small bowl, stir syrup and peanut butter until blended.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over ice cream and sprinkle with 1/2 the peanuts.
Repeat layering.
Freeze until firm, about 5 hours.
You'll love this if you like peanut butter.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Pour liquid into flour mixture.
Blend with spoon.
This can be re-rolled without toughening.
Can be kept in refrigerator for up to a week.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: caramel corn snack mix
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine popcorn, cereal, pretzels, and pecans.

title: glady's ripe tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer slow, about 2 to 3 hours.
Pour into hot jars and seal while hot.
Serve with peas and butter beans or with chips and over cream cheese.

title: short-cut three bean salad
directions: Empty beans into colander.
Rinse and drain.
Combine in large mixing bowl with rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and add olives.
Toss into dressing to coat.
Cover and chill 4 hours or overnight.
Salad keeps well for 1 week.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer, blend for 2 minutes, pour filling in pie crust and place pies on a cookie sheet to ensure bottom of pie becomes crisp.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Pour into a 9-inch pie shell; dot with butter.
Add top crust. Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.

title: corn moussaka
directions: Spread corn in an ungreased 10 x 6 x 2 baking dish.
In medium skillet, brown hamburg.
Drain off excess fat.
Add flour. Stir one minute.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic and cinnamon.
Pour over corn in dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine eggs and cottage cheese.
Spread over meat mixture.
Top with parmesan and mozzarella cheese.
Bake 10-15 minutes more. Serves 6.

title: squash pudding
directions: Mix everything together and bake at 350° in lightly greased casserole dish for 1 hour.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, beat until creamy.
Add applesauce and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients that have been sifted together, add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: ice cream
directions: Combine and put in freezer and add whole milk until freezer is full (approximately 1 quart).

title: sunny banana pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°; cool.
Slice bananas into crust.
Gradually add 1/2 cup milk to softened cream cheese, mixing well until blended. Add pudding mix and remaining milk.
Beat slowly for 1 minute. Pour into crust and chill.

title: green pea dip
directions: Cream the soup and mayonnaise together.
Add onion and soy sauce.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain oranges and pineapple.
Take juice and enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Bring to a boil and add jello and gelatine.
Cool and add to sour cream and soft cream cheese.
Put in blender and blend until smooth.
Put in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Add drained oranges, pineapple, whole berries, juice and pecan pieces.
Stir until well blended.
Pour in dish, 9 x 14-inches.
Chill until firm.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and baking powder.
Add other ingredients and mix. Pour batter in an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sees fudge
directions: Place sugar, marshmallows and milk in heavy pan.
Mix well and bring to boil.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and butter until butter is melted.
Then add nuts and vanilla.
Blend well.
Put onto buttered plate and chill.

title: cooked dressing
directions: Add to sugar the flour, salt, pepper and egg; stir all together.
Add water to vinegar and then add to mixture; stir well.
Cook over medium heat until thick.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip with beater.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch glass pan and sprinkle graham cracker crumbs to form crust.
Pour cream mixture in glass pan.
Spread over crust.
Make lemon pie filling as desired on package.
Pour over cream cheese filling and top with Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken no peek
directions: Spread raw rice in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix both cans of soup, water and butter in bowl, then pour mixture over rice. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over rice.
Place chicken on top. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: punch bowl salad
directions: Bake cake as directed; cool.
Tear into pieces.
Make layers of cake, jello, pudding, strawberries and Cool Whip.
Repeat until used.
Save some Cool Whip for top.
Place whole strawberries on top.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Turn oven to 350° and butter a casserole dish.
Brown sausage and diced onions.
Slice potatoes and alternate sausage, potatoes and cheeses.
Pour 1 cup milk over.
Cover and bake until potatoes are done.

title: white salad
directions: Dissolve cold water and Knox gelatine.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and water together and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Mix the two mixtures together and refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Add the sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix very well with wire whisk.
Pour in mold or bowl (spray with Pam first); refrigerate until set.
When removed from mold, garnish with desired fruit.
(Ex:
cherry pie filling)

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans. Toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons flour; set aside. In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, bananas and vanilla. Beat at low speed until blended, scraping bowl occasionally. Add remaining flour, allspice and next 3 ingredients; beat at low speed until well blended. Fold in blueberries. Pour batter into prepared pans. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread the bean dip in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sour cream, taco mix and mayonnaise and spread on top of bean dip.
Spread diced olives and onions on top of bean dip. Spread on taco sauce. Top with diced tomatoes. Add cheese and refrigerate for at least 3 hours. Serve with nachos.

title: toll house pie
directions: Mix eggs, flour, sugar and butter.
Stir in chocolate bits. Bake in a 9 inch pie crust for one hour at 325°.
Serve with vanilla ice cream, whipped cream or Kool Whip.

title: peanut butter carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, both sugars, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Beat eggs, oil and vanilla in a small bowl. Add to dry ingredients and blend. Stir in carrots, chips and nuts (raisins). Pour into greased
and floured 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until tester comes out clean. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cheese; mix everything with cheese, except pecans. Form into 2 balls and roll in pecans.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill for several hours.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: texas soggy sheath cake
directions: Melt 2 sticks oleo, cocoa and water.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add flour, sugar and salt; add to egg mixture.
Then add that to oleo mixture.
Add soda to flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Ice when taken out of oven.

title: fruit cake
directions: Line
small loaf pans.
After greasing them, line and grease again.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: great bread!
directions: Boil water or milk; pour over grains and cool.
Combine yeast, warm water and honey; add to cooled grains.
Add salt, whole wheat flour and 4 to 5 cups white flour, mixing thoroughly.
Add rest of flour, 1/2 cup at a time, kneading until dough is smooth and elastic.
(Don't add too much flour; keep in mind that you may not need the entire amount.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Reserve half cheese and crackers for topping.
Fold all the other ingredients together.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Spread softened butter or margarine in bottom of 9-inch square cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly on butter or margarine and arrange peaches on top of the mixture.
Prepare cake batter according to package directions, then pour batter over fruit.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 minutes.
Loosen sides of cake with spatula.
Place serving plate over cake and turn upside down immediately.
Allow parts to rest over cake before removing.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: chicken with mushrooms and rice
directions: In a skillet, brown chicken pieces on all sides in oil for 15 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add rice to skillet along with onion.
Cook, stirring, until rice is lightly browned.
Add mushrooms, carrots and water and place chicken atop rice mixture.
Season the chicken with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until chicken and rice are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cottage cheese sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and chill for several hours. Yields 6 sandwiches.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and flour in saucepan.
Add vinegar and beet liquid. Stir to remove any lumps.
Place over medium heat.
Cook until thick.
Add beets, butter and salt to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix together and beat well the following: soup, mayo, onion and eggs.
Grease casserole dish.
Layer in the following order:
broccoli, cheese and small amount of egg mixture.
Repeat, finishing with egg mixture.
Top this with dressing mix.
Pour oleo over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is toasted and mixture is hot.

title: ratatouille(ra-ta-tooey)
directions: Cut everything into bite size pieces.
In large covered pot, first cook tomatoes (with juice) and onion until onion is soft. Add zucchini, eggplant and green pepper.
Cook for approximately 15 minutes.
Do not let eggplant and zucchini become mushy!
Can be served hot or cold.
If cold, add a dab of sour cream on top. Good anytime of year, but excellent with fresh summer produce!

title: blarney stone-kissed cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until well blended.
In a separate bowl, stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture, beating until well blended.
Divide dough in half.
Place each half on a separate sheet of waxed paper.
With hands, shape each half into a log with squared sides, about 7-inches long and 2 1/4-inches wide. Wrap each log in waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until firm, at least 8 hours.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, shortening, margarine, egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix in flour and salt until dough holds together.
Beat egg white slightly.
Dip each ball of dough into egg white; roll in nuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Press thumb deeply in center of each cookie.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 9 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet and fill thumbprint with jelly or jam.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add pineapple, strawberries and pecans.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Pour half of mixture into mold and let congeal.
When firm, spread sour cream over this layer. Pour the other Jell-O mixture over sour cream.
Congeal overnight.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream together oleo, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in the flour and nuts.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Pinch dough off into small balls.
Roll and put on a sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 - 30 minutes.
Do not brown.
Let cool to handle. Roll in powdered sugar.
Shake off excess sugar and place on wax paper to cool.
When cool store in cookie tins with wax paper between layers.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook dry noodles per directions and drain.
Mix Good Seasons per directions.
Add Salad Supreme.
Mix all with noodles.
Serve at room temperature.

title: welsh braised leeks
directions: Melt butter in a wide, shallow saucepan, add the chopped onion and saute until it is pale gold and softened.
Trim and wash the leeks thoroughly; add them to saucepan.
Pour in a cup of good stock and simmer, covered, until leeks are just tender.
Serve on slices of buttered toast.
Serves 4.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger and 1/2 cup onions.
Stir in catsup, chili powder and salt.
Add beans, simmer 5 minutes.
Spread mixture in shallow casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup onions, olives and cheese.
Microwave until cheese melts or bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips and salsa.

title: ecuadorian treat - baked bananas
directions: Cut bananas lengthwise and place in a lightly greased baking dish.
Arrange orange sections over the bananas and sprinkle with sugar.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the fruit. Bake in a hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold. Delicious with chicken or to serve as dessert.
Makes 8 servings.

title: willidean's potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes, onion and celery with water and cook until tender.
Add the cream of mushroom soup, celery soup, milk and cream cheese.
Simmer until heated to serving temperature.

title: picante sauce
directions: Grind tomatoes, onion and pepper in food processor.
Mix all ingredients in large pot and bring to boil, stirring often.
Cook for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Scald jars.
Heat lids.
Put sauce into jars and seal tightly.
Turn jars upside down until sauce cools.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Blend 1 cup boiling water in lemon Jell-O; cool until slightly thick. Whip 1/2 cup of whipping cream; blend with mayonnaise. Add to Jell-O and whip until well blended. Add 1 cup shredded corned beef; mix well. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into salad mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: holly bars
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine and marshmallows.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Pour mixture over corn flakes and mix well. Drop by teaspoon in clusters or shape into wreath.
Add red hot candies as berries.

title: better than basic broccoli
directions: Arrange broccoli in buttered casserole dish.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise and cheese.
Spoon over top of broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs or crushed croutons around edge of dish.
Top with grated cheese over entire top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jennie's shredded wheat bread(5 loaves)
directions: Pour water over Shredded Wheat.
Add shortening, salt, sugar and molasses.
Stir to mix.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve the yeast in 1 cup warm water with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon salt. Add to mixture.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead 10 minutes.
Let rest 30 minutes and knead again.
Raise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into 5 loaves and put into pans.
Raise again about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: english plum pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding enough flour to make quite stiff.

Take cloth of muslin, wring out of boiling water and spread in bowl. Sprinkle cloth with 3/4-inch thickness of flour. Put in mixture. Add 3/4-inch flour on top and sides so that mixture is entirely covered by flour.
Tie the cloth about 1-inch above mixture to allow expansion from boiling.

title: party punch
directions: Add enough ginger ale to make a gallon.
Tint with food coloring.
Float ice cream, sherbet or ice ring in bowl.
Add sugar to taste.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with honey graham crackers, then pour cherry filling over the crackers, then a layer of Cool Whip on top.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Oil baking dish, line with tortillas, torn up.
Add chicken and onions.
Mix soup, broth and Rotel.
Pour over the top.
End with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Mix and cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil. Mixture will be bubbling all over top.
Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat and add chocolate chips, pecans and vanilla. Spread in 8-inch square dish, buttered.
Cool and cut.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with water until dissolved.
Cool.
Add fruit and Coke and let gel in refrigerator.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Boil water and	pour
over
jello; mix until dissolved. Add pineapple and blueberries.	Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and congeal.

title: green rice
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, milk, cheese, bell pepper, onion, rice and soup.
Put into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: deer jerky
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
Brush meat on both sides.
Put on cookie sheet or hang from toothpicks on rack in oven.
Heat oven to lowest temperature setting.
Baste and turn meat often.

title: sour cream strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture into a large mold or a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm while other half remains at room temperature.
Let sour cream come to room temperature; spread on top of congealed mixture.
Top with remaining gelatin mixture.
Chill again until firm.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Slice all vegetables and put in a large bowl that has a cover. Mix the remaining ingredients together; pour over sliced vegetables. Cover and chill overnight. Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix in order given.
Put 1/2 bag potato chips (crushed) into mix.
Other 1/2 goes on top.
Bake in greased casserole dish for 20 minutes at 450°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together and pat in bottom of 10-inch spring pan and up sides about 2-inches.

title: spicy fruit punch mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fill ceramic or glass mugs with water.
Heat in microwave oven on Full power for 1 1/2 minutes per mug, or until steaming hot.
Stir in 2 rounded teaspoonfuls of mix per cup.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill for 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Leave out for 24 hours, then put into refrigerator.
Use in 6 to 7 days or feed it
with same proportions given.
Use 1 1/2 cups in your favorite recipe for bread, or as recipe states.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all of above ingredients and put in a greased 12 x 18-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin sheet cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs, then add baking soda.
Add dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin.
Bake in a 14 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch cake pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: In nonstick skillet, saute onions and meat.
Drain.
Leave onions and meat in skillet and set aside.
In small bowl, mix Ricotta, 1 1/2 tablespoons cheese and a dash of salt and pepper. Spread over meat and onions in skillet.
Spread uncooked noodles evenly over Ricotta.
In small bowl, mix tomatoes, spices and water.
Pour over noodles.
Cover pan tightly and return to heat. Simmer on medium heat about 30 minutes or until noodles are cooked.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese over all. Yield:
4 servings.

title: delicious round steak
directions: Use Dutch oven or electric skillet.
Cut steak into serving pieces.
Salt and pepper to taste; dredge with flour.
Brown in small amount of oil, then add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Turn on low heat; cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Yields 2 cups of rich, creamy gravy and very tender steak.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place corn-on-the-cob still in the husks in a sink of water. Let soak for about 1 hour.
Remove from water and let drain for a couple of minutes.
Place on grill and close.
Cook for about 30 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and cream.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Bake in Bundt pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Don't open door until 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in salted water.
Drain.
In a large saucepan, melt oleo and stir in flour to make paste.
Add milk and salt.
Cook 15 minutes (sauce will be thin).
Drain water from vegetables and add vegetables to sauce.
Continue cooking 10 to 15 minutes more.
(May add pepper).

title: ultimate crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese at high speed of a mixer until smooth. Add yogurt, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and hot sauce; beat well. Stir in green onions, water chestnuts and crabmeat. Yield: 4 cups. Serving Size: 1/4 cup.

title: joan's hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Put in large shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine potato chips with cheese and almonds; sprinkle on top.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 25 minutes or until heated.
Serves 8.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In large heavy pan, brown beef in 1 tablespoon shortening. Pour off fat.
Stir in broth, wine and thyme.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Simmer 1 hour more. Gradually blend 1/3 cup water into 1/4 cup flour until smooth. Slowly stir into stew.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients well. Chill in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; stir well.
Chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion, tomato sauce and spices. Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine and beat together for 2 minutes the cake mix, eggs, oil, water and coconut flavoring.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Mix together until smooth the coconut syrup and condensed milk.
Poke holes in warm cake with fork.
Pour syrup-milk mixture over cake.
Set in fridge overnight.
Beat whipping cream.
Frost top of cake with whipping cream; sprinkle with coconut.
Serve chilled.
Enjoy!

title: party beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bean pot (or covered dish).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan butter brittle
directions: Microwave sugar, syrup and butter 3 minutes on high.
Stir in nuts.
Mix well.
Microwave 7-12 minutes on high, checking several times to make sure nuts don't burn.
Add baking soda and quickly stir.
Pour onto greased surface.
Cool and break into pieces. Store in air-tight container.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar; beat in eggs.
Add flour, salt and cinnamon.
Dissolve baking soda in sour milk and add to mixture. Then add vanilla and apples.
Bake in small greased loaf pan.
Add cinnamon topping before baking.
(Dough will be stiff.)

title: beef filled crescent rolls
directions: Saute beef and onion in butter until beef is lightly browned. Add remaining ingredients, except rolls.
Warm the mixture but do not boil.
Remove from heat and cool to room temperature. Separate rolls and spread mixture on each roll.
Roll into crescent shape and bake according to directions.
Slice each roll into bite-size pieces and serve hot.

title: asparagus loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheeses, dressing, olives and red pepper.
Lightly grease mini muffin tin and press 1 wrapper in each cup.
Brush with oil.
Bake for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from tins.
Place on baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake for 5 minutes.

title: spicy wine pot roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper; place in slow cooking pot. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meat.
Cover and cook on medium 5 to 6 hours.
Remove meat and slice.
Thicken sauce with flour dissolved in a small amount of water; serve over meat.

title: italian green beans
directions: Cook beans until partially tender; drain and saute in olive oil, 1 clove garlic and basil or parsley.
Add salt and pepper. Cook until tender.

title: crispy baked chicken(low-fat)
directions: *Be creative and experiment with other seasonings.

title: pickled jalapeno peppers
directions: Pack equal amounts of peppers, carrots and onion slices into hot sterilized jars; place 1 tablespoon olive oil in each jar. Heat
water,
vinegar
and
salt
to
a boil.
Pour over peppers, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Seal and process in hot water
bath for
minutes.
Let
set 3 weeks before using. Makes 2 pints.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix together the margarine and brown sugar.
Add the corn flakes, coconut and walnuts.
Press 2/3 of the mixture into 2 pie plates.
Add 1/2 gallon slightly melted ice cream and press in remaining 1/3 of the mixture.
Freeze for several hours.
Serve with hot fudge sauce.

title: banana delight
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish, ungreased.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese and add chopped onions, butter, salt and mix well.
Pat mixture into a ball.
Roll in dried beef.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Great for parties.

title: crab and rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill for several hours or overnight. Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: curried pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in a soup kettle.
Saute onion and apple until tender (5 minutes).
Stir in pumpkin; remove from heat.
Process or blend until smooth; return to kettle.
Add chicken broth and cream.
Whisk in seasonings.
Heat gently and serve.

title: mints
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Knead until mixture is easy to shape into balls; form mint balls.
Press balls flat with fork.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients all at once until smooth. In another bowl, mix coconut, strawberries and pecans. Pour half of strawberry mixture in cake batter. Save the remainder for icing. Add 1 box of powdered sugar and 1/2 stick margarine to remaining mixture. Mix well. This is the icing. Cake will make 3 layers. Bake at 350° until cake pulls from side of pan. Cool and ice.

title: minute man broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Combine soup, eggs, cheese, onion and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix and dot with butter.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, melted butter and cinnamon. Press into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil beets in a large pan. Cool with cold water. Peel and slice beets. Add ingredients to beets and bring to a boil for 45 minutes. Cool and serve.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in ice cream maker.

title: colleen's caramel corn
directions: Spread popcorn in large shallow pan. In a heavy pan, stir together sugar, margarine, Karo and salt. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Continue cooking, without stirring, 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake in
a 250° oven, uncovered, 1 hour, stirring 3 or 4 times.
Break apart when cool. Store in tightly closed container.

title: eloise's bean stuff
directions: Brown ground beef and drain excess grease.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in butter.
Add beans, barbecue sauce, brown sugar and browned ground beef.
Cook until vegetables and ground beef is done.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put in a baking dish (a quiche dish is a good size).
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with Melba rounds or small crackers.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with pizza sauce.
Sprinkle 2 cups shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Mix Bisquick, eggs and milk.
Pour evenly over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jumbo chocolate-raisin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease six 3-inch muffin pan cups.
In a 1-quart saucepan over very low heat, melt butter and chocolate, stirring constantly, until blended and smooth.
Remove from heat; set aside to cool slightly.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In small bowl, beat milk, egg and vanilla to blend well.
Stir in cooled chocolate mixture.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture, stirring until just blended; stir in raisins and chocolate chips.

Pour batter into prepared pan and bake 30 minutes until tops of muffins spring back when pressed. Serve warm or at room temperature, sprinkled with confectioners sugar accompanied with Strawberry Butter.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg yolks with a small amount of water. Add to hot pineapple juice.
Stir and cook until thick.
Add butter.
Cool.

title: apple - bran streusel muffins
directions: Combine flour, cereal, sugar, baking powder, allspice and salt in a small bowl; combine egg whites, milk and oil.
Add flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Fold in apple.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups.
Sprinkle with streusel topping.
Bake about 20 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm.

title: country gravy
directions: Mix well over low heat.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle brown sugar in bottom of well-greased pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Dot with butter.
Melt mixture over low heat.
Drain pineapple.
Place slices in pan with cherry in center of each.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream the shortening; add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour mixture, a little at a time, alternately with milk.
Pour batter over fruit. Bake 1 hour or until light brown.
Turn upside down on serving plate at once.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 9 servings.

title: cheese-stuffed hamburger roll
directions: Simmer onion in 1/3 cup boiling water for 5 minutes.
Pour over bread.
Combine meat, egg and seasonings.
Pat out in 14 x 8-inch rectangle on waxed paper.
Spread bread mixture over and sprinkle 1 cup of the cheese on top.
Roll and place in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 70 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese and bake 2 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings

title: cheese cookies
directions: Melt butter and cheese; add flour and hot sauce.
Stir well and add Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
These freeze real good.

title: pasta salad italiano
directions: Place pasta, zucchini, carrot, olives, pepperoni, and green onions in large bowl.
Stir vinegar into evaporated milk until thickened.
Blend in mayonnaise and parmesan cheese.
