Pour over pasta mixture, and stir gently until well coated.
Chill.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: recipe for 6 pie shells(extras)
directions: Sift the flour with the salt.
Mix the Crisco into the mixture with pastry cutter or fingers until it becomes size of small peas. Add the ice water.
Form into 6 balls.
Makes enough for 6 pie shells.
May be kept in freezer for future use.
Will defrost in about 40 minutes for use.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with dressing; dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar and milk until it forms a soft ball.
Add butter. Remove from heat and beat. Gradually add chopped dates. Continue beating and slowly add the nuts.
Add vanilla last.
Pour into buttered square cake pan.
Allow to cool until solid before cutting into 1-inch square pieces.

title: date-orange cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour; add alternately with buttermilk with soda added.
Add nuts and dates (roll them in part of the flour).
Cook in tube or loaf pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl except dressing; just before serving, add dressing.
Mix well.
Serves 15.

title: feed a lot cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour into 17 x 11 x
1/2-inch
pan.
Spread drained pineapple on cooled cake. Mix
cream cheese, milk and pudding.
Pour over pineapple.	Spread top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle thick with coconut. Keep in refrigerator overnight.

title: real cajun red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans and pork in salted water slowly for 45 minutes. Add vegetables, seasonings and tomato sauce.
Cook slowly for another hour, stirring occasionally.
Crumble and add sausage, for extra body, and cook 45 minutes more.
Cool, but do not necessarily refrigerate.
Reheat and bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer gently for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over boiled rice.
Great for a party meal!

title: cold carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots to medium done, rinse in ice water.
Put carrots, green pepper strips and sliced onions in a bowl.
Boil soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. After completely boiled, pour over carrots, peppers and onion. Keeps in refrigerator for 3 weeks.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; stir into mixture.
Form dough into balls about the size of walnuts.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain and cool. Add eggs, onion and relish. Chill and serve.

title: henrietta
directions: Cook and drain noodles; set aside.
Brown beef with onion, green pepper and celery.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Butter casserole dish.
Layer noodles, then meat mixture. Repeat and top with cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar, then add Cool Whip.
Next, add pineapple, drained, and cherries which you have drained on paper towels, then add nuts.
Mix all together and chill.

title: pigs in a blanket(i admit that this recipe has a weird name.)
directions: In a large roaster, place meat and vegetables, except carrots. Sprinkle seasonings on top, and add water to cover roast.
Place lid on roaster and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove, add carrots, then bake an additional 30 minutes, or until meat and potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.

title: spinach wontons
directions: Cook spinach, drain well and press dry.
Melt butter in skillet and add onion and saute until tender.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Place one teaspoon spinach mixture in center of each wonton.
Lightly brush edges with water.
Fold over and press edges together.
When all are filled, place several at a time in hot oil and fry 30 seconds on each side or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
These freeze well.

title: grandmother's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix eggs, raisins and vanilla.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Be sure to follow directions.

title: swedish tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat 1/2 cup powdered sugar, margarine and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour, almonds and salt; mix until dough holds together.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Crumble 1/2 of brownies in bottom of casserole.
Layer one container Cool Whip on top of brownies, then layer 1/2 of chocolate mousse and 2 crumbled Heath bars.
Repeat layers, using remainder of crumbled brownies, 1/2 container Cool Whip, remaining mousse and 2 crumbled Heath bars.
Top with 1/2 container Cool Whip.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: turkey or chicken bake
directions: Cook turkey; measure out 2 cups.
Combine turkey, soup, peas, 1/2 cup milk, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch or	medium baking dish.
Blend egg and 1/2 cup milk with corn muffin mix until moistened (slightly lumpy).
Spread over mixture. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: mushroom masterpiece
directions: Saute garlic and mushrooms in oil.
Add tomatoes and spices. Simmer for at least 2 hours.
Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Serve sauce over spaghetti.
Top with cheese and dip Italian bread in sauce on side.
Enjoy!

title: mayonnaise dressing
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Put in enough water to soften this and then stir in eggs, then vinegar to taste.
Add the rest of the water and butter.
Cook until the right consistency.

title: chewy goody bars
directions: Put margarine, peanut butter, brown sugar, honey and vanilla in saucepan.
Place on stove on medium-low.
Stir mixture constantly until it comes to a boil.
Turn heat off, remove pot and place on heatproof surface.
In large mixing bowl, combine cereal, raisins, peanuts and cinnamon.
Pour syrup over cereal mixture.
Stir mixture with wooden spoon until everything is coated with syrup mixture.
Pour cereal mixture into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Press evenly into corners.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: sweet potato pineapple casserole
directions: Beat all ingredients together manually or with electric mixer until fairly smooth.
Butter large baking dish (approximately 3 quart).
Place 1/2 mixture in dish; dot with marshmallows, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven, dot top with marshmallows and replace in oven for about 10 minutes, or until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil. Add dry Jell-O.
Mix thoroughly and set aside to cool. Add 2 cups of buttermilk and the oranges.
Now blend in the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: tourtiere(french meat pie)
directions: Put first 9 ingredients in a pot; mix well.
Bring up to simmer.
Cook for 30 minutes, covered, stirring occasionally. Take cover off and cook for 10 more minutes.
If there is a lot of liquid, remove about half, taking some of the liquid to make a thick mashed potato.
Add potato mixture to the meat; pour into bottom crust.
Put on the top crust; put in 6 to 7 vent holes. Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes; lower to 350° for 30 minutes. Take out when light brown on the top.
You may vary the proportions according to your taste.

title: scallops au gratin
directions: Start oven at moderate 350°.
Rub a baking dish with butter or margarine.
Rinse scallops; drain.
Cover with cold water in saucepan and heat slowly to boiling; drain.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with a spoon, then add next 4 by hand and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle a bag of marshmallows all over cake.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Take out of oven and let cool completely.
Mix last 4 ingredients and pour over cooled cake.

title: palitaw
directions: Combine rice flour and 1 1/2 cups water; blend thoroughly. With floured hands, shape dough into egg-sized ovals and flatten with thumb.

title: slow-cooked swiss steak
directions: In large zip lock bag, combine flour, salt and pepper. Add the steak, seal bag and toss to coat. Place chopped onion in a greased slow cooker. Top with steak, celery and tomato sauce. Cover and cook on low for 6-8 hours or until tender.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Cook sugars and sour cream to a hard ball stage.
Remove from fire and add vanilla and pecans.
Stir until hardened.
Spread and separate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs. Beat until creamy. Add dry ingredients: flour, baking soda, nutmeg, salt and cinnamon. After all is mixed, add vanilla. Fold in apples last.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: broccoli with olives and lemon zest
directions: Combine the garlic and olive oil.
Set aside.
Steam the broccoli in a small amount of water until crisp-tender.
Let cool, then slice the stalks and separate the florets.
Combine the broccoli, olives, lemon zest, oil and garlic.
Add black pepper. Serve at room temperature.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix ingredients with tablespoon of mayonnaise (enough to coat).

title: filled cupcakes
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Set aside.

title: memoo's lace cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour in egg, butter and vanilla.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Drop 1 teaspoon dough onto aluminum far apart.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from foil.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in three layers.
Cool.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine green beans, milk, soup, dash of salt, dash of pepper and garlic.
Mix well.
Put into ungreased casserole dish.
Place French fried onion on top of mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend shortening, margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.

title: chocolate velvet cream
directions: Crust:
Combine crumbs and butter.
Press into bottom of 9 or 9 1/2-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat all together.
Put into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shortbread squares
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Bake on greased cookie sheet (17 x 11-inches) until golden in color, about 12 minutes at 325°. Immediately from oven, cover with chocolate chips.
Put back into oven until chips are soft, about 8 seconds.
Spread chips with spatula and cut immediately.

title: western dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in quart jar and shake until sugar dissolves.	Keep refrigerated and shake well before using.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar and buttermilk until well blended. Combine dry ingredients and blend into egg mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Add blackberries gently.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add oil and eggs; mix well.
Stir in strawberries and nuts.
Pour into three greased and floured large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Good when spread with strawberry cream cheese to make sandwiches.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cut in shortening into flour and salt until particles are size of small peas.
Sprinkle in water, one tablespoon at a time, tossing with fork until all flour is moistened and pastry almost cleans side of bowl (1 to 2 teaspoons water can be added if necessary).

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, cut in large chunks.
Layer in large baking pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread sour cream on potatoes and top with Hellmann's spread.
Crumble bacon and then top with thick slices of Velveeta.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: In double boiler, beat the egg.
Slowly add the sugar.
Next, add the lemon juice.
Cook, stirring, until thick and smooth. Cool.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Mix the fruit and cooked sauce together.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serves 5 as a salad.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: natural dyes to color easter eggs
directions: Place uncooked eggs in a glass or stainless steel 2-quart saucepan.
Add enough water to come to at least 1-inch above eggs. Add 1 tablespoon vinegar and desired natural material.
Cover saucepan and bring to a boil; reduce heat and let simmer 20 minutes.
Rinse with cold water and let air dry.
Polish eggs with vegetable oil for a vibrant sheen and enjoy.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil corn on cobs for 2 minutes, then cut off cobs.
Measure and mix all ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Process 15 minutes in boiling water.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients and fry like pancakes.

title: fruit ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar and vanilla in bowl and mix thoroughly with mixer.
Pour into can.
Add condensed milk and fruit; stir well.
Add dairy milk to fill line on can and stir. Makes 4 quarts.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line 2 unbaked 9-inch pastry shells with pecans.
Blend all other ingredients with a mixer.
Pour half of mixture into each pie shell over pecans.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Turn oven down to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: louisiana fruit salad
directions: Combine in large bowl.
Best if prepared the night before use.

title: baked pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir pineapple into egg-sugar mixture.
Fold in bread cubes.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with ham.
Very tasty. Serves 6.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve sugar, salt and Crisco in hot water in very large bowl; add cold water.
Dissolve yeast in very warm water.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, stirring well.
Knead at the end until dough forms a ball.
Grease top and sides of bowl.
Let rise until double in size.
Knead and let rise again.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook, clean and dice the shrimp.
Toss together shrimp, celery (diced), onion, egg, seasonings, lemon juice and mayonnaise. Quarter tomatoes and place each on lettuce bed.
Arrange salad on tomato.
Makes 4 servings.

title: country steak
directions: Fry cube steak.
Put into slow cooker.
Cook gravy; mix onion soup, brown gravy or mushroom gravy.
Add cornstarch or flour. Pour gravy into slow cooker with steak.
Let cook for 2 or 3 hours, stirring every 30 or 45 minutes.
Cook on low.

title: layered cheeseburger bake
directions: In pan, brown ground beef with onion.
Mix in bacon, salt, pepper, celery soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Place a layer of potatoes in the bottom of a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with half of the meat and soup mixture and half of the cheese. Repeat the layers.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: honey chicken
directions: Heat ingredients over low heat.
Brush over the chicken and bake in a 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine first 5 ingredients, mix well.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, oil and strawberries.
Add to dry ingredients, mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix until smooth with mixer.
Add milk until as smooth as you like.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well together with spoon.
Do not mix with blender.

title: yankee doodle apple dessert
directions: Mix and sift cake flour,
brown sugar, baking powder, salt, mace and cinnamon.
Stir in unbeaten
egg
and
vanilla.
Fold in apples and walnuts.
Turn in well greased 8-inch
pie
pan.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients well; pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375 degrees until golden brown.
You can add fruits or nuts if desired.

title: old fashioned strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together and rub well together with the butter, then add the egg, well beaten, then the milk and work lightly, just enough to make a smooth dough.
Roll out lightly. Place in a deep layer cake tin that has been greased and bake in 375° oven.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash, clean and cut up fryer. Mix the 3 seasonings together. Can pour this mixture back into the original seasoning containers. Shake the seasoning
mixture onto the chicken as if you were salting it. Store unused seasoning for future use. Place seasoned chicken in baking dish and cover. Bake at 350 for 1 hour.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Layer ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan (macaroni, meat, pepperoni, mushrooms, spaghetti sauce, then cheese).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix together and add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Stir together sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add water and butter. Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until thick.
Add vanilla. Serve over hot biscuits.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cut chicken up and mix with sour cream and mushroom soup.
Put into a casserole dish and cover top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle poppy seed over cracker crumbs and bake for 30 minutes or longer at 325°.

title: stir-fried pork tenderloin
directions: In medium bowl mix, soy sauce, sherry, ginger, cornstarch, sugar and pork.
In Wok, add oil (enough to cover bottom).
Cook vegetables and salt. Stir often, cook for 5 min. Add water if necessary. Remove vegetables. Add more oil and cook pork, 3-4 min. until no longer pink. Add vegetables.
Heat through. Serve with Long Grain Wild Rice.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Brown the hamburger and drain.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender.
Makes approximately 36 to 40 cups.

title: banana cream pudding
directions: Heat together milk and sugar.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold milk.
Add to sugar and milk; stir until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook only until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat. Slice and add bananas.
Chill in sherbet glasses.
Top with 1 tablespoon whipped cream.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together; stir into shortening mixture alternately with milk.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Roll immediately in melted butter, then in cinnamon sugar.
Makes 12.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour.
Cook until bubbly.
Add light cream, broth and milk.
Cook, stirring, over medium heat to the beginning of a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in Worcestershire sauce and Cheez Whiz until melted.

title: glorious iced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and add one gallon of water.

title: low-fat bean lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix beans and spaghetti sauce.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Using 1/3 of each ingredient, arrange in this order in a 9 x 13-inch pan:
noodles, spaghetti sauce, bean sauce, cottage cheese or Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers 2 more times.
Makes six 4 x 4-inch servings.

title: sweet and sour asparagus
directions: Boil vinegar, salt, sugar, spices and water. Pour over asparagus. Cover. Chill for 24 hours. Drain. Serve. Yield: 6 servings.

title: english trifle
directions: Slice cake in 1/2-inch thick fingers; make into sandwiches. Fill with preserves.
Place half, spoke like fashion, in 1 1/2-quart serving dish.
Sprinkle on half the sherry.
Repeat with remaining cake, alternating with bottom spokes and sherry.
Quarter apricot halves; place atop.
Prepare pudding, following package directions, but using 3 cups milk.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
While pudding is hot, pour over dessert.
Chill well. Before serving, center with whipped cream and nuts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked fish fillets with onions and potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in half lengthwise, then crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Quarter onion and cut into 1/4-inch slices. Place onions and potatoes into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and drizzle with 3 tablespoons of melted margarine.
Bake in 400° oven for 35 minutes or until golden, turning potatoes with spatula at least once.
Dip fish fillets in remaining melted margarine and coat with crumbs.
Arrange over top of potato mixture; sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Bake an additional 15 minutes or until fish flakes.

title: sausage bread
directions: In large frying pan, saute onion until transparent, then add skinned sausage (crumbled).
When sausage and onions are done, add red wine, along with the chopped spinach.
Cook for a few minutes more.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
Serve with any raw vegetables, chips or cubes of ham, chicken, turkey or pork.

title: miniature tomato sandwiches
directions: Slice tomatoes and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Spread mayo and cream cheese mixture on bread. Add a tomato slice and top with bread. (Optional: Two tablespoons real bacon bits and a dash of onion powder.) Make mix a day ahead. Great for showers and weddings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, pecans, coconut and cake mix (mixed following directions on box).
Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese and oleo.
Spoon on top of cake mix in little blobs.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fruited cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple, cherries, orange peel and ginger.
Refrigerate until firm enough to shape into a ball.
Fold in finely chopped walnuts.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with sliced pears or apples.
Dip the slices in lemon juice to retard discoloration.
Serve cheese ball at room temperature.
Encircle the cheese ball with the fruit slices to serve.

title: old fashioned fruit cake
directions: Cut up nuts, cherries and pineapple.
Cover with 1 cup flour (plain).
Add cake spices to mixture and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Add soda to syrup and stir into butter mixture.
Add flour and wine alternately, small amount at a time, until ingredients are completely mixed.
Stir in fruit mixture.
Bake at 275° in 2 (9 or 10-inch) cake pans for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Spray a 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs, reserving 1 tablespoon for garnish. Set aside.
Bring apples, water and spices to a boil in a large saucepan.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in gelatin and pudding mix until well blended. Bring to a full boil on high heat.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Spoon into pie plate. Sprinkle with reserved graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Garnish each serving with 1 tablespoon yogurt.
Makes 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into loaf.
Top with ketchup or a strip of bacon.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn-on-the-cob(microwave oven)
directions: *Corn may be husked and silked before cooking.
Wrap in wax paper or place in a covered glass dish.
Cook, following times, rotating halfway through cooking.
Season.
(It won't be as sweet as that cooked in the husk.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Stir apples and sugar together.
Add dry ingredients and stir well.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir into apple mixture.
Stir in dry ingredients and pecans.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: dill weed dip(for vegetables)
directions: Mix together;
let
sit overnight in refrigerator.
Use as dip for fresh vegetables or as a salad dressing.

title: praline cake
directions: Mix pecans, brown sugar, butter and corn syrup in small bowl, spread on bottom of ungreased 13x9 inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour cake mix carefully over pecan mixture. Bake as directed on package.
Run knife around edges of pan to loosen immediately; turn pan upside down onto heat proof serving tray or wire rack.
Leave pan over cake about 5 minutes, remove pan.

title: crab dip
directions: The night before, mix softened cream cheese, lemon juice and chopped onion.
Mold into serving dish and refrigerate.
Wash fresh parsley and let dry.
Pre-party, layer shelled crab meat and layer of chili sauce with hot sauce to taste.
Top with parsley. Refrigerate prior to serving.
Serve with crackers or French bread rounds.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Dissolve 1 package of Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thick.
Dissolve second package of Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add ice cream and stir until melted.
Pour into serving bowl.
Chill 1 hour or until set, but not firm.
Arrange berries on Jell-O ice cream mixture.
Top with clear Jell-O.
Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Bake cake.
Then add glaze.
Top with layer of pineapple and a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat with layers of glaze, pineapple and Cool Whip until pan is full.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: zucchini-lime salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice; add enough water to make 1 1/4 cups.
Set pineapple aside.
Bring liquid to a boil; add lime Jell-O, stirring until Jell-O melts.
Add lime juice; chill until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in pineapple, zucchini and Cool Whip.
Pour into lightly oiled 6-cup mold.
Cover and chill until firm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: In 9 x 13-inch dish, spread bean dip on bottom, then chopped onions, pepper, tomatoes and grated cheese.
Top with olives and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put on warming tray to serve. Tostado chips should be served with this.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put cheeses in bowl; let stand at room temperature until soft. Blend.
Add onion and Worcestershire.
Gradually add milk.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Bring rhubarb and sugar to a boil and boil for 10 minutes. Add the Jell-O and let stand on heat until Jell-O is dissolved. Pour into jars and seal. Makes 5 pints.

title: cran-orange banana bread(low-fat and sugar-free)
directions: Combine cranberries and sweetener to taste; set aside. Combine orange juice, bananas and eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add cranberries to this mixture.
Combine dry ingredients; add to batter.
Beat 1 minute.
Fold in raisins.
Spoon into a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until knife inserted at center comes out clean.
Makes 20 servings.

title: natto puffs
directions: Lightly beat an egg in a medium sized bowl; sprinkle in the flour.
Mix with chopsticks or fork, then add the natto, stirring to separate the beans as much as possible.
Stir in the onion and garlic (if using).

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Butter a 10-inch pie pan.
Peel, core and slice apples; put in pie pan.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Cream the soft margarine, 1 cup sugar, salt and egg.
Add flour to creamed ingredients.
Mix and spread over apples. Sprinkle walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
When cake is done, punch small holes in it.
Mix coconut, sugar and sour cream together.
Pour over cake while it is hot.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolks, beating after each addition.
Add soda to sour cream and mix, then add to butter mixture.
Add flour, mix well.
Add flavor.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Sift flour twice.

title: apple cake
directions: Add sugar to sliced apples and let stand 10 minutes or longer. Sift flour and spices.
Blend oil and eggs together; pour into apple mixture.
Add flour mixture all at once.
Stir with a wooden spoon until well blended.

title: turtle cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix as usual.
Pour 1/2 of cake mix in pan and bake 15 minutes.
In pot on stove, melt caramels with butter and milk.
Pour over hot cake.
Next sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips on top of caramel mixture.
Pour remainder of cake on top and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: jiffy baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients, except for bacon.
Place in 1-quart casserole dish.
Place bacon strips on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well and bake in a hot skillet in 425° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: curried fruit for breakfast casserole
directions: Drain all fruit.
Add sugar and curry powder to butter. Arrange fruit in layers in casserole dish.
Pour butter mixture over fruit.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Put in casserole dish; add broth, chicken soup, peas and carrots and mix together.

title: bacon and potato hot pot
directions: Grease a large casserole dish with 1 tablespoon of the butter. Place a third of the potato slices on the bottom of the dish. Add salt and pepper.
Top with half of the bacon.
Sprinkle half of the parsley on the bacon.
Add half of the onion slices. Season with salt and pepper.
Place a third of the potato slices over the onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Repeat the layers with the remaining bacon, parsley and onion slices and put the remaining potatoes in an overlapping layer on top.
Add salt and pepper.

title: mashed potato cake dated 1868
directions: Cream together egg yolks, butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, soda, cinnamon, ginger and cocoa powder.
Add mashed potatoes, nuts and raisins. Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: silly putty
directions: Mix this together with your hands.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: spinach and sausage quiche
directions: In a large skillet brown sausage and drain well.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add drained spinach, cheese, seasonings and sausage and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour for 1 large or 30 minutes for 2 small.
I prefer 2 small.
Large serves 6.
Two small serves 12.

title: swedish toast
directions: Bake in 3 greased loaf pans for 45 minutes at 300°, then 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and wrap in wax paper.
Keep for a couple of days at least.
Slice thin, place on cookie sheet and toast in a 300° oven for 20 minutes or more.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes.
Add brown sugar, white sugar and margarine.
Stir until margarine melts.
Add eggs and mix well. Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add flour to sugar mixture and mix well.
Add 1/2 of the chocolate chips.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and the rest of the chocolate chips on top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: geometric shortbread
directions: Blend butter with other ingredients, stirring until dough holds together.
Press evenly in an ungreased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes (until lightly golden).
While still hot, prick surface all over with fork and sprinkle powdered sugar over top.
Cut into squares with sharp knife.
When cool, I put them in an airtight pan to preserve the crispness.

title: hershey's oatmeal crispies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in oblong pan.
Bake, cool and eat.
Can add chocolate frosting if desired.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, melt the margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Mix together and press in pan.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool before cutting.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until done, then put in a casserole dish alternating carrots, chicken soup, chicken pieces and onions. Salt and pepper.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: judy cornell's butter cutout cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter.
Add sugar a little at a time.
Gradually work in flour, then milk, vanilla and butter extract.
Turn dough out on a floured board and knead about 1/2 minute.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut with floured cutters in shapes desired.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes.
Watch closely.
These should be almost white when they are ready to take out.
They do not get brown.

title: weight watchers' cake
directions: Beat yolks of 6 eggs plus the whole egg together.
Add sugar, lemon extract and milk powder.
Whip egg whites until stiff; fold into egg yolks.
Spoon into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Stir together until well blended. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin and applesauce pie
directions: Cook raisins, sugar, 1 cup water, salt, butter and lemon juice for 5 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 2 or 3 tablespoons cold water; add to raisin mixture along with applesauce.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add extract.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Top with strips of pastry and dot with sugar and butter.
Bake 25 minutes in hot oven (400° to 450°).

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and paprika. Separate eggs.
Beat yolks.
Blend with corn.
Stir in flour mixture.
Beat egg whites.
Fold into corn mixture.
Heat shortening in a heavy skillet.
Drop spoonfuls into hot fat.
Turn to brown.
Serve hot.

title: shepherd pie
directions: Spray lightly with Pam a 3-quart Corning Ware or casserole dish and set aside.
Boil potatoes until tender.
Mash with little butter and milk.
Set aside.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with cracker crumbs, pressing it into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 5 to 7 minutes in a 350° oven. Let cool completely.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli well.
Mix
cheese,
diced, and margarine with broccoli.
Place in 9 x
9-inch buttered baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers.
Top with dabs of margarine. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, pineapple and walnuts together. Pour batter into 2 greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes before removing.
Cream the cream cheese, confectioners sugar, margarine and vanilla together.
Spread frosting on top of cooled layers and between layers.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crescent turkey squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of butter until smooth.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; press perforation to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup turkey mixture in center.
Pull four corners up.
Twist and seal. Brush with 1 tablespoon butter and dip in crouton crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Chop broccoli fine.
Cook in half the broth.
Salt to taste. Make paste with melted oleo and flour.
Add milk slowly.
Cook to thicken.
Add broccoli mixture with remaining broth.
Simmer to thicken.
When serving, add bits of bacon and shredded Swiss cheese.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: okie yummy
directions: Mix flour, pecans and margarine in a mixing bowl and press firmly in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread ingredients in pan in the order listed.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: okshen kugel
directions: Cook noodles as directed on the package; drain well.
Stir in remaining ingredients and half of the melted margarine.
Place in a greased casserole and pour over the remaining melted margarine. Bake, uncovered, at 350° (180°C) for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Add milk and dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in rhubarb.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and bring to a hard rolling boil.
Then add peanuts.
Cook until nuts look parched, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix well all but last 2 ingredients to form a stiff dough. Roll into balls a little smaller than a walnut and place on waxed paper.
Refrigerate 3 or 4 hours.
Melt semi-sweet chips with Crisco.
Insert toothpicks into top of peanut butter balls and dip into chocolate.
Leave a circle of peanut butter showing.
Let cool on waxed paper.

title: layered salad
directions: Toss together lettuce, cauliflower and peas.
Layer bacon, then onion, then Good Seasons.
Spread over top mayonnaise, then cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: wild rose hip jelly
directions: Remove blossom ends of hips; split and remove balls of seeds. Crush fruit thoroughly.
Add water.
Bring to boil and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Pour into cloth bag in large bowl; tie top of bag and hang over bowl until all juice has drained from bag.
This should yield about 4 cups juice.

title: ground beef soup
directions: Cook ground beef by scrambling it.
Add remaining ingredients and let come to a good boil, then simmer for 15 minutes!

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 can oranges with juice, eggs and oil. Beat together 3 minutes.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and Wesson oil, 7-Up and eggs. Beat well mixed.
Bake at 350°.

title: dill carrots("for a crowd")
directions: Using a Steam Jacketed kettle, on #8, simmer carrots in chicken stock until tender.
Add sugar, dill, salt, white pepper and heavy cream.
Bring to a low boil and thicken with a 1 to 1 cornstarch and water mixture until sauce just coats carrots.
Do not overcook carrots!!
Yields 1 (6 1/2-inch) size pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add syrup and salt; beat well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: danish cheesecake
directions: Cream butter, 6 tablespoons sugar, beat in egg.
Add 2 cups flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Pat into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Mix together remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Chill well before serving.

title: tuna rice royal
directions: Combine tuna, rice, celery and onions. Blend soup, milk and cheese.
Heat. Stir into tuna mixture. Season to taste.
Turn into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with topping. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef bouillon casserole
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Put in rice; then add both cans of soup.
Lay mushrooms in; add margarine.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and cocoa. Add alternately with milk.
Add nuts.
Drop with teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Spread slightly.
(These are a soft cake-like texture.) Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. I always frost them with powdered sugar frosting, plain or add cocoa for chocolate frosting.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: veggie pancakes
directions: Stir ingredients together. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet. Dip by 1/3 cup at a time in hot oil and cook until golden brown. Top with salsa and sour cream.

title: quick cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternating with milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and pineapple in 13 x 9-inch pan. Layer dry cake mix on top of fruit, covering evenly.
Cover entire cake with nuts, then with squares of butter.
Bake one hour until brown at 350°.
Makes 12 servings.
Delicious warm with ice cream.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend into Marshmallow Creme.
Thin with milk to desired consistency.
Add cherry juice (optional). Serve with fresh strawberries, grapes, pineapple chunks and apple slices.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Set out a large skillet, having a tight fitting cover.
Wash, cut off stems, ends, slice and set aside.
Chop okra and set aside.
Chop onion and green pepper (about 1/2 cup).
Add onions and green pepper; cook over medium heat until onions are transparent.
Add sliced okra and 2 cups canned tomatoes, cut up in small pieces.
Add salt and pepper to your taste.
Simmer, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes or until okra is tender.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix 1/4 cup sugar, 1 cup chopped pecans and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in heavy saucepan or microwave oven.
Add powdered sugar and milk, stirring until dissolved.
Bring to a hard boil.
Cook for 20 minutes or to a soft ball stage at 240°. Turn off heat and let set a few minutes.
Add Marshmallow Creme and butter.
Stir and beat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Cut before it gets too hard.

title: bread pudding for two
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, milk and raisins.
Blend in bread.
Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.
